      <data key="d1">The article discusses the fourth edition of &quot;Discovering Statistics Using IBM SPSS Statistics&quot; by Andy Field, highlighting its comprehensive approach to teaching statistics in an engaging manner. It emphasizes updates to content, enhanced accessibility features, and the integration of digital resources, including online assignments and mobile study tools, making it suitable for a wide range of disciplines.</data>
      <data key="d2">G76</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1992419399">
      <data key="d1">This article provides an overview of data clustering, an unsupervised classification method that groups patterns into clusters, highlighting its significance in exploratory analysis across various research disciplines. It discusses a taxonomy of clustering techniques, recent advancements, and key applications such as image segmentation and information retrieval, aiming to offer accessible insights for practitioners in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G77</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2130942839">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel end-to-end approach for sequence-to-sequence learning using Deep Neural Networks, specifically employing multilayered Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks to translate between English and French. The method demonstrates significant performance improvements, achieving a BLEU score of 34.8 on the WMT'14 dataset, surpassing traditional phrase-based systems and effectively handling long sentences and word order variations.</data>
      <data key="d2">G78</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2122111042">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the nearest neighbor decision rule in pattern classification, explaining how it assigns classifications to unclassified samples based on previously classified points, and explores the relationship between probability error and optimal classification bounds in multi-category scenarios. It highlights the implications of this method for machine learning and data classification, emphasizing its effectiveness in various applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G79</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962858109">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Grad-CAM, a technique for generating visual explanations from Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) by utilizing gradient information to create localization maps that highlight important image regions related to specific predictions. This method enhances the transparency of CNN models across various applications, including classification, captioning, and visual question answering, while also providing insights into model behavior and improving generalization.</data>
      <data key="d2">G80</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2133097426">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;The Scree Test For The Number Of Factors&quot; presents a statistical method for determining the appropriate number of factors in multivariate analysis, discussing its applications in various fields such as personality assessment, machine learning, and biostatistics. It explores the theoretical foundations and practical implications of the scree test, alongside comparisons with other factor analysis techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G81</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4295312788">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses PyTorch, a deep learning library that successfully combines usability and performance through its imperative, Pythonic programming style, making it easy to debug and efficient for hardware accelerators like GPUs. It highlights the architectural principles behind PyTorch's implementation and demonstrates its performance across various benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G82</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964015378">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a scalable semi-supervised learning approach using graph convolutional networks, which efficiently process graph-structured data by leveraging localized spectral graph convolutions. Experimental results on citation knowledge datasets demonstrate that this model significantly outperforms existing methods in terms of classification accuracy.</data>
      <data key="d2">G83</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2121647436">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a face recognition algorithm called &quot;Fisherface,&quot; which effectively handles variations in lighting and facial expressions by utilizing a class-specific linear projection method. It compares this approach to the traditional eigenface technique, demonstrating that Fisherface achieves lower error rates in facial recognition tasks, particularly in challenging conditions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G84</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1746819321">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive introduction to Gaussian processes (GPs) in machine learning, covering both theoretical and practical aspects for researchers and students in applied statistics. It addresses supervised learning for regression and classification, explores various covariance functions, discusses model selection from Bayesian and classical perspectives, and connects GPs to other statistical techniques, while also including algorithms, examples, and supplementary resources.</data>
      <data key="d2">G85</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2031611770">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses FastTree 2, an enhanced tool for inferring phylogenetic trees from large sequence alignments, highlighting its improved accuracy and efficiency through the incorporation of advanced algorithms like subtree-pruning-regrafting (SPRs) and the CAT approximation. It emphasizes FastTree's ability to handle extensive datasets, achieving significant speed and accuracy compared to traditional methods, making it a valuable resource for researchers in phylogenetics.</data>
