    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1821462560">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a method for improving machine learning performance by compressing the knowledge of multiple neural network models into a single, more efficient model, known as knowledge distillation. This approach not only simplifies deployment for large-scale applications but also demonstrates significant performance enhancements, particularly in tasks like classifying fine-grained categories.</data>
      <data key="d2">G87</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4294214983">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the kappa statistic as a key measure for assessing interrater reliability, highlighting its advantages over traditional percent agreement methods by accounting for chance agreement. It also addresses the challenges in interpreting kappa values, particularly in health research, where the acceptability of certain kappa thresholds may be questioned.</data>
      <data key="d2">G88</data>
    </node>
