      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Hierarchical Linear Models: Applications and Data Analysis Methods&quot; discusses the use of hierarchical linear models in statistical inference and data analysis, highlighting their applications in high-dimensional statistics, latent modeling, and machine learning. It emphasizes the importance of these models in various fields, including applied mathematics and data science, while also addressing computational methods for effective data modeling and analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G89</data>
    </node>
