      <data key="d1">The article introduces MobileNets, a class of efficient convolutional neural networks designed for mobile and embedded vision applications, utilizing depth-wise separable convolutions to create lightweight models. It highlights the models' ability to balance latency and accuracy through global hyper-parameters, demonstrating strong performance in various tasks such as object detection and fine-grain classification compared to other popular networks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G101</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2059147403">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses &quot;micro-checker,&quot; a Windows-based software designed to identify and correct genotyping errors in microsatellite data, addressing issues such as null alleles and scoring errors that can bias population genetic analyses. It highlights the software's capabilities in estimating null allele frequencies and adjusting genotype frequencies for more accurate genetic analysis, and it is available for free download.</data>
      <data key="d2">G102</data>
    </node>
