      <data key="d2">G104</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963470893">
      <data key="d1">The article presents SRGAN, a novel generative adversarial network designed for single image super-resolution that effectively recovers fine texture details at large upscaling factors. By introducing a perceptual loss function and leveraging deep residual networks, SRGAN significantly improves the quality of super-resolved images, achieving results that are closer to high-resolution images compared to existing methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G105</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1680392829">
      <data key="d1">The article reviews and compares accuracy estimation methods, specifically focusing on cross-validation and bootstrap techniques for model selection. It presents findings from extensive experiments demonstrating that ten-fold cross-validation is often more effective than leave-one-out cross-validation for selecting classifiers, even in real-world datasets.</data>
