      <data key="d1">This article introduces compressive sampling, a groundbreaking approach that challenges traditional sampling methods based on Shannon's theorem, demonstrating that it is possible to accurately recover signals or images from significantly fewer samples than the Nyquist rate would suggest. It explores the theoretical foundations of compressed sensing and its implications for fields such as computer science, statistics, and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G113</data>
