      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to robust face recognition using sparse representation techniques, addressing challenges such as varying expressions, illumination, and occlusion. It proposes a classification algorithm based on l{1}-minimization that enhances feature extraction and demonstrates improved performance over traditional methods through extensive experiments on publicly available databases.</data>
      <data key="d2">G117</data>
