      <data key="d2">G119</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2099085143">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of PLINK 1.9, a second-generation toolset for genome-wide association studies (GWAS) that addresses the challenges posed by larger and more complex datasets, including probabilistic calls and multiallelic variants. It highlights significant performance improvements through advanced algorithms and bit-level parallelism, enabling researchers to conduct essential genetic analyses without requiring high-end computing resources.</data>
      <data key="d2">G120</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2096684396">
      <data key="d1">The article examines the reliability of Differences-in-Differences (DD) estimates in econometric studies, highlighting the inconsistency of standard errors when using serially correlated outcomes over multiple years. Through simulations and comparisons of various methodologies, it reveals that conventional approaches often underestimate variability, while suggesting that bootstrap methods and specific asymptotic approximations can improve accuracy under certain conditions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G121</data>
    </node>
