      <data key="d1">This book offers a comprehensive exploration of feed-forward neural networks within the context of statistical pattern recognition, covering essential concepts, modeling techniques, and error minimization algorithms. It also addresses key topics such as learning generalization, data processing, and feature extraction, concluding with a discussion on Bayesian applications in neural networks.</data>
