    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2549139847">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a modular network architecture called ResNeXt for image classification, which utilizes aggregated residual transformations to enhance performance by focusing on cardinality as a key factor in model capacity. The authors demonstrate that this approach improves classification accuracy on the ImageNet-1K dataset and outperforms traditional methods of increasing depth or width, achieving notable success in the ILSVRC 2016 competition.</data>
