    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2109255472">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the introduction of Spatial Pyramid Pooling (SPP) in deep convolutional networks, which allows for variable-sized input images, enhancing recognition accuracy and efficiency. The proposed SPP-net architecture demonstrates significant improvements in classification performance across various datasets, achieving state-of-the-art results while reducing computational time compared to traditional methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G130</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2953384591">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses TensorFlow, a large-scale machine learning system that utilizes dataflow graphs for computation across various devices, including CPUs, GPUs, and TPUs. It highlights TensorFlow's flexibility for developers, its strong support for deep neural network inference, and its widespread adoption in both research and production environments, particularly within Google services.</data>
      <data key="d2">G131</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2117228865">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces ORB, a fast binary descriptor that serves as an efficient alternative to traditional methods like SIFT and SURF for feature matching in computer vision tasks. ORB is highlighted for its speed and robustness, demonstrating significant performance improvements in various real-world applications, including smartphone patch tracking.</data>
      <data key="d2">G132</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2612445135">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces MobileNets, a class of efficient convolutional neural networks designed for mobile and embedded vision applications, utilizing depth-wise separable convolutions to create lightweight models. It highlights the models' ability to balance latency and accuracy through global hyper-parameters, demonstrating strong performance in various tasks such as object detection and fine-grain classification compared to other popular networks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G133</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962862931">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a unified framework called SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) for interpreting model predictions, addressing the challenge of understanding complex models like ensemble and deep learning. It introduces new additive measures and theoretical results that unify six existing interpretation methods, demonstrating improved computational performance and alignment with human intuition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G134</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2295107390">
      <data key="d1">The article explores how the global average pooling layer in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) enhances their ability to localize discriminative features in images, achieving significant performance in object classification without the need for bounding box annotations. Through various experiments, the authors demonstrate that this technique allows CNNs to implicitly focus on relevant image regions while solving classification tasks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G135</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2112315008">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a comprehensive comparison of 16 methods for predicting species distributions using occurrence data, highlighting the effectiveness of novel machine learning techniques over traditional models. The findings suggest that these new methods can better handle the noise and sparsity often found in ecological data, offering improved predictions for conservation and ecological applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G136</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1985588649">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Glide, a novel docking method that enhances the accuracy of ligand positioning in protein receptors by employing a systematic search and energy optimization process. It evaluates the method's performance against existing techniques, demonstrating superior docking accuracy through rigorous assessments and comparisons with other established methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G137</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2138484437">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the effective use of neural networks for identifying and controlling nonlinear dynamical systems, highlighting novel multilayer recurrent configurations and adaptive schemes. It discusses both theoretical concepts and practical applications, demonstrating the feasibility of these methods through simulation results.</data>
      <data key="d2">G138</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2101927907">
      <data key="d1">This article provides an introduction to artificial neural networks, exploring their structure, design principles, and applications in pattern classification and clustering algorithms. It highlights recent advancements in the field and discusses how simple neuron-like components can be utilized to enhance performance in tasks such as speech and image recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G139</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2125389028">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Conditional Generative Adversarial Nets (CGANs), an extension of Generative Adversarial Nets that incorporates conditional data to enhance the generation of outputs, such as MNIST digits based on class labels, and explores their potential applications in multi-modal learning and image tagging.</data>
      <data key="d2">G140</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1560724230">
      <data key="d1">&quot;Learning with Kernels&quot; offers a thorough introduction to Support Vector Machines (SVMs) and kernel methods, highlighting their theoretical foundations and practical applications across various fields. The book caters to readers with basic mathematical knowledge, guiding them through both fundamental concepts and the latest advancements in machine learning algorithms that are increasingly replacing traditional neural networks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G141</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2560609797">
      <data key="d1">The article presents PointNet, a novel neural network designed to directly process point clouds for 3D classification and segmentation, addressing the challenges posed by irregular geometric data structures. By maintaining permutation invariance and demonstrating strong performance across various applications, PointNet offers an efficient and effective solution for tasks in computer vision and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G142</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2131774270">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of bidirectional recurrent neural networks (BRNNs), which enhance traditional RNNs by allowing simultaneous training in both forward and backward time directions. It presents experimental results demonstrating that BRNNs outperform other methods in regression classification tasks on artificial data and phoneme recognition from the TIMIT database, while also detailing modifications for efficient estimation of conditional posterior probabilities.</data>
      <data key="d2">G143</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1519266993">
      <data key="d1">The article presents MUSCLE, an advanced multiple sequence alignment method that enhances both biological and computational efficiency, introducing a faster variant called MUSCLE-fast for high-throughput applications. It compares MUSCLE's performance against existing programs like CLUSTALW and MAFFT, demonstrating significant improvements in speed and accuracy across various alignment benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G144</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2143612262">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the application of deep recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for speech recognition, highlighting their potential to improve performance through end-to-end training methods and Long Short-term Memory architecture. It reports a significant achievement in reducing test set error to 17.7% on the TIMIT phoneme benchmark, marking a notable advancement in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G145</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2170747616">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the enhancements made to the CD-HIT program, which is designed for clustering biological sequences, to accommodate the growing volume of next-generation sequencing data. The new version features an accelerated parallelization strategy that significantly improves processing speed, allowing it to efficiently handle large datasets in much shorter timeframes compared to previous iterations.</data>
      <data key="d2">G146</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2162915993">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel method for recognizing natural scene categories through a spatial pyramid matching technique, which enhances traditional bag-of-features approaches by partitioning images into sub-regions and analyzing local features. This method demonstrates significant improvements in accuracy on challenging categorization tasks, particularly on the Caltech-101 database, and provides valuable insights into various image representation techniques in computer vision.</data>
      <data key="d2">G147</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2118020653">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the rise of machine learning techniques in automated text categorization over the past decade, highlighting their effectiveness and efficiency compared to traditional knowledge engineering methods. It provides a survey of key approaches within this paradigm, focusing on document representation, classifier construction, and evaluation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G148</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2107726111">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive survey of reinforcement learning, focusing on its principles and applications within computer science and machine learning. It covers historical context, key challenges such as exploration versus exploitation, and practical implementations, while drawing parallels to psychological concepts.</data>
      <data key="d2">G149</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2102201073">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel method for flexible regression modeling of high-dimensional data using Multivariate Adaptive Regression Splines, which employs product spline basis functions to automatically determine key parameters. This approach combines the advantages of recursive partitioning with the ability to produce continuous models, effectively capturing complex relationships and interactions among multiple variables.</data>
      <data key="d2">G150</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963207607">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the phenomenon of adversarial examples in machine learning, arguing that the primary cause of neural networks' vulnerability to these inputs is their linear nature, rather than nonlinearity or overfitting. It presents a new method for generating adversarial examples and demonstrates its effectiveness in reducing test set error in a maxout network on the MNIST dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G151</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3018757597">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses YOLOv4, a state-of-the-art object detection model that combines various advanced features such as Weighted-Residual-Connections and Cross-Stage-Partial-connections to achieve optimal speed and accuracy, reaching 43.5% average precision on the MS COCO dataset at approximately 65 frames per second. It emphasizes the importance of practical testing and theoretical justification for improving Convolutional Neural Network performance in real-time applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G152</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2099244020">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses bilateral filtering, a technique used in image processing that effectively smooths gray and color images while preserving edges by combining nearby pixel values based on their spatial and photometric similarities. It highlights the advantages of this noniterative and local method over traditional filters, particularly in maintaining perceptual quality in images.</data>
      <data key="d2">G153</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2395611524">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development and application of Fully Convolutional Networks (FCNs) for semantic segmentation, highlighting their ability to process images of arbitrary sizes and produce correspondingly-sized outputs. It details how FCNs improve upon previous models by utilizing a skip architecture to combine features from different layers, achieving significant performance gains on various benchmark datasets while maintaining efficient inference times.</data>
      <data key="d2">G154</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2112076978">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses experiments conducted to evaluate a new boosting algorithm called AdaBoost, which aims to reduce classification errors in machine learning. It compares the performance of AdaBoost with Breiman's bagging method across various benchmarks and examines its effectiveness in a nearest-neighbor classifier for an OCR problem, particularly focusing on the impact of a pseudo-loss method.</data>
      <data key="d2">G155</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2124379907">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses rank correlation methods, exploring their theoretical foundations, significance testing, and various applications in fields such as biostatistics, data science, and machine learning. It covers topics like tied ranks, paired comparisons, and the use of ranking algorithms for parameter identification and statistical analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G156</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2118978333">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive review of the challenges and advancements in learning from imbalanced data, particularly in large-scale systems across various domains such as finance and security. It discusses the nature of the problem, evaluates state-of-the-art technologies and assessment metrics, and highlights future opportunities and challenges in the field of data science and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G157</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964350391">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the advancements in image recognition performance through the use of very deep convolutional networks, specifically focusing on the Inception-v4 and Inception-ResNet architectures. It highlights the benefits of combining these architectures with residual connections, demonstrating significant improvements in training speed and classification accuracy on the ImageNet challenge.</data>
      <data key="d2">G158</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1522734439">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach for learning spatiotemporal features using 3D convolutional networks (3D ConvNets), demonstrating their superiority over 2D ConvNets and highlighting the effectiveness of a homogeneous architecture with small convolution kernels. The study reveals that the learned C3D features, when combined with a simple linear classifier, achieve competitive performance on various benchmarks while maintaining computational efficiency and ease of training.</data>
      <data key="d2">G159</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2155482699">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the application of the Marquardt algorithm for nonlinear least squares in training feedforward neural networks, demonstrating its efficiency compared to a conjugate gradient variable learning rate algorithm on various function approximation tasks, particularly when the network has a few hundred weights.</data>
      <data key="d2">G160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2954996726">
      <data key="d1">This article presents a comprehensive survey on image data augmentation techniques for deep learning, highlighting their importance in addressing the challenges of limited data availability in fields like medical image analysis. It explores various augmentation methods, including geometric transformations and generative networks, and discusses their impact on model performance and dataset quality.</data>
      <data key="d2">G161</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2124181495">
      <data key="d1">The article explores various resampling techniques, including the Jackknife and Bootstrap methods, to estimate bias and variance in statistical models, emphasizing their applications in computer science, machine learning, and data science for model refinement and forecasting. It also discusses advanced concepts such as the Infinitesimal Delta Method, Influence Function, and Cross-Validation, providing insights into nonparametric confidence intervals and other sampling strategies.</data>
      <data key="d2">G162</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1565377632">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive introduction to data mining, covering its definition, challenges, and historical context, as well as various techniques such as classification, clustering, and association analysis. It also explores advanced topics, including anomaly detection and the evaluation of different algorithms, making it a valuable resource for understanding the principles and applications of data mining in data science and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G163</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2955425717">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses EfficientNet, a novel approach to scaling Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) by uniformly adjusting their depth, width, and resolution using a compound coefficient, resulting in significantly improved efficiency and performance. The EfficientNet models, particularly EfficientNet-B7, achieve state-of-the-art accuracy on ImageNet while being smaller and faster than previous ConvNets, demonstrating their effectiveness across various datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G164</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1885185971">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a deep learning approach for single image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which directly learns the mapping between low and high-resolution images. It highlights the method's efficiency, state-of-the-art restoration quality, and ability to optimize all layers jointly, while also addressing the reconstruction of three color channels for improved overall image quality.</data>
      <data key="d2">G165</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3035524453">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Momentum Contrast (MoCo), a novel approach for unsupervised visual representation learning that utilizes a dynamic queue and moving-averaged encoder to enhance contrastive learning. MoCo demonstrates competitive performance in ImageNet classification and excels in various downstream tasks, often surpassing traditional supervised pre-training methods in detection and segmentation benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G166</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2153947402">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces FactoMineR, an R package designed for multivariate data analysis, highlighting its ability to handle various types of variables, incorporate supplementary information, and provide automated descriptions of dimensions from exploratory analyses, along with a user-friendly graphical interface within the Rcmdr environment.</data>
      <data key="d2">G167</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2107878631">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of training recurrent neural networks (RNNs) using gradient descent for tasks that involve long-term dependencies in input/output sequences, highlighting the difficulties that arise as the duration of these dependencies increases. It also explores the trade-offs between efficient learning and retaining information over extended periods, suggesting potential alternatives to standard gradient-based methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G168</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3099206234">
      <data key="d1">The article presents FaceNet, a novel system for face recognition and clustering that learns to map images into a compact Euclidean space, allowing for efficient measurement of face similarity. By utilizing deep convolutional networks and a unique online triplet mining method, FaceNet achieves state-of-the-art accuracy on benchmark datasets while maintaining a highly efficient representation of only 128 bytes per face.</data>
      <data key="d2">G169</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1515851193">
      <data key="d1">&quot;Introduction to Reinforcement Learning&quot; by Richard Sutton and Andrew Barto offers a comprehensive overview of the fundamental concepts and algorithms in reinforcement learning, tracing the field's history and recent advancements while requiring only a basic understanding of probability. The book covers essential topics such as Markov decision processes, deep reinforcement learning, and applications in artificial intelligence and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G170</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963684088">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of Deep Convolutional Generative Adversarial Networks (DCGANs) as a method for unsupervised representation learning in computer vision, highlighting their ability to learn hierarchical representations from image data and their applicability to various tasks beyond image generation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G171</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2121016876">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development and accuracy assessment of the base-calling program &quot;Phred,&quot; which automates the processing of DNA sequencer traces. It highlights Phred's superior performance in reducing error rates compared to existing software, thereby addressing the growing demand for accurate DNA sequencing in the context of large-scale genomic projects.</data>
      <data key="d2">G172</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963524571">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the limitations of existing action classification datasets and introduces the Kinetics dataset, which significantly enhances action recognition capabilities by providing a larger and more diverse collection of videos. It also presents a new Two-Stream Inflated 3D ConvNet (I3D) model that improves classification performance on smaller benchmarks, demonstrating the effectiveness of leveraging extensive data and advanced architectures in video understanding.</data>
      <data key="d2">G173</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2162273778">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a real-time algorithm designed for the accurate detection of QRS complexes in ECG signals, achieving a 99.3% detection rate by utilizing digital analysis techniques and adaptive threshold adjustments to minimize false detections from interference. The algorithm's effectiveness is enhanced by a specialized bandpass filter, allowing for increased sensitivity in various heart rate morphologies.</data>
      <data key="d2">G174</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2146502635">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel family of adaptive subgradient methods that enhance online learning and stochastic optimization by leveraging previously observed data geometry to improve gradient-based learning. It discusses the development and analysis of these methods, demonstrating their effectiveness in empirical risk minimization problems and showing that they outperform traditional non-adaptive algorithms.</data>
      <data key="d2">G175</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2102625004">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses an adaptive background mixture model for real-time tracking in image sequences, focusing on background subtraction techniques that utilize a mixture of Gaussians to effectively segment moving regions. It highlights the model's robustness against various challenges such as lighting changes and clutter, demonstrating its reliability through continuous operation over 16 months in diverse weather conditions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G176</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2998216295">
      <data key="d1">The article provides an overview of variable and feature selection techniques, highlighting their significance in various research fields that deal with high-dimensional datasets, such as machine learning, image analysis, and pattern recognition. It emphasizes the importance of these methods in improving model performance and efficiency in data-driven applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G177</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1510073064">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses kernel methods as a versatile framework for pattern analysis, highlighting their application in various fields such as bioinformatics, text analysis, and image analysis. It serves as both a practical toolkit for practitioners and an introductory resource for students and researchers, providing insights into algorithm development and the necessary mathematical concepts.</data>
      <data key="d2">G178</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2132549764">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive review of statistical pattern recognition, highlighting its primary goal of classification through both supervised and unsupervised methods. It discusses the evolution of techniques, including the rise of neural networks, and addresses ongoing challenges in recognizing complex patterns, while also exploring emerging applications in fields such as data mining and face recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G179</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964153729">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the intriguing properties of deep neural networks, highlighting their expressiveness and state-of-the-art performance in tasks like speech and visual recognition. It discusses two key findings: the lack of distinction among high-level units in the networks, suggesting that semantic information is not contained within the layers, and the existence of imperceptible perturbations that can significantly disrupt the network's output, indicating a discontinuous nature in input-output mappings.</data>
      <data key="d2">G180</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962914239">
      <data key="d1">The article presents V-Net, a fully convolutional neural network designed for volumetric medical image segmentation, specifically targeting 3D MRI volumes of the prostate. It introduces a novel training approach using the Dice coefficient to address class imbalance and demonstrates improved performance and efficiency compared to traditional methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G181</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2950635152">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel RNN Encoder-Decoder model for statistical machine translation, which utilizes two recurrent networks to encode input sequences into fixed-length vector representations and decode them into target sequences. The model is jointly trained to enhance translation accuracy by incorporating phrase pair probabilities, demonstrating improved performance and the ability to learn meaningful linguistic phrases.</data>
      <data key="d2">G182</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2172000360">
      <data key="d1">The article compares various methods for extending support vector machines (SVMs) from binary to multiclass classification, focusing on both &quot;one-against-all&quot; and &quot;one-against-one&quot; approaches, as well as directed acyclic graph (DAGSVM) methods. It presents performance evaluations of these techniques, highlighting that the &quot;one-against-one&quot; DAGSVM method is more suitable for practical applications due to its efficiency in requiring fewer support vectors.</data>
      <data key="d2">G183</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2117812871">
      <data key="d1">&quot;Pattern Recognition and Neural Networks&quot; is a comprehensive 1996 book that explores the statistical foundations of pattern recognition and machine learning, featuring extensive case studies and real data sets to enhance understanding. It serves as both a valuable resource for experienced researchers and an accessible introduction for non-specialists, covering diverse applications across various fields such as remote sensing, engineering, and medicine.</data>
      <data key="d2">G184</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1991001144">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Z-factor, a simple statistical parameter designed to evaluate and validate high-throughput screening (HTS) assays, facilitating the identification of active compounds from large chemical libraries by providing a standardized measure of assay quality and suitability for comparison.</data>
      <data key="d2">G185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962784628">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach to neural machine translation (NMT) that enhances the handling of rare and out-of-vocabulary words by utilizing subword units instead of a fixed vocabulary, demonstrating improved translation performance on English-to-German and English-to-Russian tasks compared to traditional dictionary-based methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G186</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1493790738">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive overview of categorical data analysis, covering key methodologies such as two-way contingency tables, logistic regression, and loglinear models, while also exploring their applications in fields like biostatistics and machine learning. It includes historical context, statistical theory, and practical tools for data analysis, along with an appendix of chi-squared distribution values and a bibliography for further reading.</data>
      <data key="d2">G187</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2508457857">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of a deep convolutional neural network (DnCNN) for image denoising that leverages residual learning and batch normalization to enhance training efficiency and performance. Unlike traditional models that target specific levels of Gaussian noise, this approach enables blind denoising, effectively addressing various image restoration tasks such as super-resolution and JPEG deblocking while benefiting from GPU acceleration.</data>
      <data key="d2">G188</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W954331293">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a workshop titled &quot;Qualitative Research and NVivo Application,&quot; aimed at medical practitioners at USM, focusing on qualitative research stages, data collection techniques, and analysis, with an emphasis on using NVivo software for qualitative data analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G189</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963125010">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces ShuffleNet, a highly efficient convolutional neural network (CNN) specifically designed for mobile devices with limited computing power, achieving significant reductions in computation cost through innovative techniques like pointwise group convolution and channel shuffle. Experimental results demonstrate ShuffleNet's superior performance in tasks such as ImageNet classification and MS COCO object detection, outperforming other architectures like MobileNet while maintaining accuracy and achieving substantial speed improvements on ARM-based devices.</data>
      <data key="d2">G190</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963840672">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel network module designed for semantic segmentation that utilizes dilated convolutions to effectively aggregate multi-scale contextual information while maintaining resolution, thereby enhancing the accuracy of state-of-the-art models in dense prediction tasks. It also explores the potential for simplifying adaptations to further improve performance in scene understanding and image analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G191</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2025768430">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel training principle for denoising autoencoders that enhances the robustness of learned representations by intentionally corrupting input patterns. It highlights the effectiveness of this approach in improving feature learning for deep generative and discriminative models, supported by comparative experiments demonstrating its advantages in pattern classification tasks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G192</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2024650319">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Structural Equation Modeling: Concepts, Issues, and Applications&quot; provides a comprehensive overview of structural equation modeling (SEM), covering fundamental concepts, model specification, evaluation techniques, and various applications across different fields, including psychology and social sciences. It features contributions from multiple experts discussing challenges, strategies, and the use of SEM in analyzing complex relationships among variables.</data>
      <data key="d2">G193</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2145962650">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a method for robust principal component analysis that enables the exact recovery of low-rank and sparse components from a data matrix, even when a significant portion of the entries are corrupted. It introduces Principal Component Pursuit, a convex optimization approach that minimizes a weighted combination of nuclear and ℓ1 norms, and explores its applications in video surveillance and image analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G194</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1904365287">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a technique called &quot;dropout&quot; that enhances the performance of neural networks by randomly omitting a portion of feature detectors during training, which helps prevent overfitting and complex co-adaptations among detectors. This method has led to significant improvements in various benchmark tasks, including speech and object recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G195</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2630837129">
      <data key="d1">The article revisits atrous convolution for semantic image segmentation, proposing enhancements to the Atrous Spatial Pyramid Pooling module to improve multi-scale object segmentation. It details the implementation of the 'DeepLabv3' system, which achieves superior performance on the PASCAL VOC 2012 benchmark compared to previous versions and other state-of-the-art models, without the need for post-processing.</data>
      <data key="d2">G196</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2173520492">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of Deep Convolutional Generative Adversarial Networks (DCGANs) as a method for unsupervised representation learning in computer vision, highlighting their ability to learn hierarchical representations from image datasets and their applicability in various tasks beyond traditional supervised learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G197</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2158733823">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the implementation of random early detection (RED) gateways in packet-switched networks to prevent congestion by monitoring average queue sizes and selectively dropping or marking packets. It highlights how these gateways can effectively manage traffic without bias against bursty data and are designed to work alongside transport-layer protocols like TCP, with simulations demonstrating their performance benefits.</data>
      <data key="d2">G198</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962770929">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel generator architecture for generative adversarial networks (GANs) that leverages concepts from style transfer, enabling the automatic separation of high-level attributes and stochastic variations in generated images. This approach enhances image quality, improves interpolation properties, and introduces new methods for quantifying disentanglement, while also providing a diverse dataset of high-quality human faces.</data>
      <data key="d2">G199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1989702938">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive survey of face recognition technology, highlighting its advancements, applications in law enforcement, and the challenges posed by real-world conditions such as varying illumination and pose. It reviews existing literature, categorizes techniques, and discusses relevant topics including psychophysical studies and system evaluation in the context of image analysis and computer vision.</data>
      <data key="d2">G200</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1834627138">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel deep learning framework for predicting face attributes in real-world scenarios, utilizing a cascaded architecture of two convolutional neural networks (LNet and ANet) that are fine-tuned with tags. It highlights the framework's ability to improve localization and identity prediction through different pre-training strategies, revealing insights into representation and enabling training without the need for bounding boxes or landmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G201</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3096831136">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses generative adversarial networks (GANs), a type of artificial intelligence algorithm that learns to generate new data by studying training examples and their underlying probability distributions, with a particular emphasis on their success in creating realistic high-resolution images and their applications in various research settings. It also highlights the unique challenges and opportunities GANs present due to their foundation in game theory.</data>
      <data key="d2">G202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963857521">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial examples and evaluates the effectiveness of defensive distillation as a method to enhance their robustness. Despite claims of improved resilience, the authors demonstrate that their newly introduced attack algorithms can successfully compromise both distilled and undistilled networks, highlighting the need for more effective defense strategies in security-critical applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G203</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1901616594">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the rapid growth and significance of machine learning, highlighting its role in enhancing computer capabilities through experience and its applications across various fields such as healthcare, finance, and education. It discusses the advancements in algorithms and the increasing availability of low-cost computational resources that drive the adoption of data-intensive machine learning methods for evidence-based decision-making.</data>
      <data key="d2">G204</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1831050183">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the caret package in R, which provides a comprehensive suite of tools for building and tuning predictive models across various techniques, including data pre-processing and variable importance analysis. It highlights its application in computational chemistry, demonstrating the package's capabilities through real data examples and the advantages of parallel processing.</data>
      <data key="d2">G205</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2402144811">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses TensorFlow, a large-scale machine learning system that utilizes dataflow graphs to efficiently manage computation across various devices, including CPUs, GPUs, and TPUs. It highlights TensorFlow's flexibility for developers to experiment with training algorithms and its widespread application in real-world scenarios, including its use in several Google services and its status as an open-source project.</data>
      <data key="d2">G206</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2116341502">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel Graph Neural Network (GNN) model designed to effectively process various types of graphs, including acyclic, cyclic, directed, and undirected graphs, by mapping nodes into an m-dimensional Euclidean space. It discusses the development of a supervised learning algorithm for parameter estimation, evaluates computational costs, and presents experimental results that validate the model's performance and generalization capabilities across multiple scientific and engineering domains.</data>
      <data key="d2">G207</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2071559616">
      <data key="d1">This article provides an overview of the five-factor model of personality, detailing its five core dimensions—Extraversion, Agreeableness, Conscientiousness, Neuroticism, and Openness to Experience—and discussing its historical development, empirical support, and implications for individual assessment and psychological research across various cultures.</data>
      <data key="d2">G208</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4288089799">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a unified framework for transfer learning in natural language processing (NLP) that converts various text-based tasks into a text-to-text format, systematically comparing different pre-training objectives and architectures. By leveraging the &quot;Colossal Clean Crawled Corpus,&quot; the study achieves state-of-the-art results across multiple NLP benchmarks and provides resources for future research in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G209</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2118585731">
      <data key="d1">LIBLINEAR is an open-source library designed for large-scale linear classification, offering support for logistic regression and support vector machines. It features user-friendly command-line tools and extensive documentation, making it suitable for both beginners and advanced users, and is particularly efficient for handling large sparse datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G210</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2141224535">
      <data key="d1">The article presents fast and robust fixed-point algorithms for independent component analysis (ICA), combining information theoretic and projection pursuit approaches to develop new contrast functions for estimating component independence. It discusses the properties of these estimators under a mixture model and provides practical optimization techniques for enhancing robustness and minimizing variance in ICA applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G211</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963121255">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces PointNet++, a hierarchical neural network designed to improve deep learning on point sets by capturing local structures and contextual scales through recursive partitioning. This approach enhances the model's ability to recognize fine-grained patterns and adapt to varying point densities, resulting in significantly improved performance on challenging 3D point cloud benchmarks compared to existing methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G212</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2339500526">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the book &quot;Tabu Search,&quot; which delves into the meta-heuristic approach of tabu search and its transformative impact on solving a wide range of complex problems across various fields, including resource planning, telecommunications, and biomedical engineering. It emphasizes practical applications, illustrated concepts, and aims to provide accessible knowledge for researchers and practitioners in management science and computer science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G213</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1504694836">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the significance of decision tree algorithms in machine learning, particularly highlighting J. Ross Quinlan's ID3 and its successor C4.5, while also noting the release of Quinlan's new book that provides a comprehensive overview of these algorithms and their latest developments, making it a valuable resource for students in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G214</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3175752499">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces clusterProfiler 4.0, an enhanced Bioconductor package designed for the functional analysis of both coding and non-coding genomics data across thousands of species, offering a universal interface for diverse applications. It emphasizes the tool's capabilities in efficiently interpreting high-throughput omics data through updated gene annotations, visualization features, and support for multiple treatment comparisons.</data>
      <data key="d2">G215</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2242218935">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel single-image super-resolution method that leverages a very deep convolutional network, inspired by VGG-net, to significantly enhance image accuracy. By employing a unique training procedure that focuses on learning residuals and utilizing high learning rates, the proposed model achieves superior performance compared to existing methods, resulting in noticeable visual improvements.</data>
      <data key="d2">G216</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2341539131">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces deepTools2, an updated Galaxy-based web server designed for the analysis and visualization of deep-sequencing data, offering enhanced tools for bioinformatic workflows, including quality control and integrative analyses. It highlights the server's accessibility, deployment options, and the availability of a public API, making it a valuable resource for researchers in genomics and related fields.</data>
      <data key="d2">G217</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962785568">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the effectiveness of deep features from neural networks, particularly the VGG model, as a perceptual metric for assessing image similarity, revealing that these features significantly outperform traditional metrics like PSNR and SSIM across various tasks and architectures. It highlights the emergent properties of visual representations, suggesting that deep learning models capture complex aspects of human perception that simpler metrics fail to address.</data>
      <data key="d2">G218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2251939518">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Sentiment Treebank, a resource designed to enhance the understanding of semantic compositionality in sentiment analysis by providing fine-grained labels for parse trees and sentences. It presents the Recursive Neural Tensor Network, which, when trained on this treebank, significantly improves sentiment classification accuracy, achieving state-of-the-art results in detecting both positive and negative sentiments, including the nuanced effects of negation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G219</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2098685541">
      <data key="d1">This article presents a novel Partial Least Squares Latent Variable Modeling approach to accurately measure interaction effects in social science research, addressing the limitations of previous studies that often failed to provide effect sizes. Through a Monte Carlo simulation and an empirical study on electronic mail adoption, the authors demonstrate the technique's effectiveness in estimating relationships while accounting for measurement error.</data>
      <data key="d2">G220</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4297733535">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Graph Attention Networks (GATs), innovative neural network architectures designed for graph-structured data that utilize masked self-attention layers to improve upon traditional convolution-based methods. GATs effectively assign varying weights to neighborhood features without the need for complex matrix operations, achieving state-of-the-art results on multiple benchmark datasets in both inductive and transductive learning scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d2">G221</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2950354111">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Canu, an advanced tool for long-read genome assembly that enhances accuracy and efficiency in processing noisy sequencing data from technologies like PacBio and Oxford Nanopore. It highlights Canu's innovative algorithms for handling complex genomic structures and its ability to assemble high-quality genomes while reducing runtime and depth-of-coverage requirements.</data>
      <data key="d2">G222</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2014767176">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a new algorithm designed for efficiently tracing steepest descent paths from transition states in chemical reactions, utilizing constrained optimizations in mass-weighted coordinates. This second-order method has been validated through various reactions, demonstrating its ability to produce accurate reaction paths with larger step sizes while maintaining high precision.</data>
      <data key="d2">G223</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1604938182">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive overview of advancements in support vector learning, covering theoretical foundations, practical implementations, and various applications, while also discussing extensions and optimizations of kernel methods in machine learning. It features contributions from multiple experts in the field, highlighting key concepts such as function estimation, classification techniques, and the use of Bayesian approaches.</data>
      <data key="d2">G224</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2557738935">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development and validation of a deep learning algorithm designed to detect diabetic retinopathy and macular edema in retinal fundus photographs, utilizing a convolutional neural network trained on a large dataset of images graded by ophthalmologists. The algorithm demonstrated high sensitivity and specificity in identifying referable diabetic retinopathy, suggesting its potential for improving clinical outcomes in ophthalmology.</data>
      <data key="d2">G225</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2279098554">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces SqueezeNet, a compact deep neural network architecture that achieves AlexNet-level accuracy with 50 times fewer parameters and a model size of less than 0.5MB, highlighting its advantages in distributed training, bandwidth efficiency, and deployment on hardware with limited memory.</data>
      <data key="d2">G226</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2797532987">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive overview of linear regression analysis, covering topics such as simple and multiple regression, model adequacy checking, diagnostics for leverage influence, and variable selection. It also explores advanced concepts like polynomial regression, multicollinearity, and the application of statistical methodologies in various fields, including econometrics and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G227</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2016053056">
      <data key="d1">The article presents an extensive evaluation of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for large-scale video classification, utilizing a dataset of 1 million YouTube videos across 487 classes. It explores various approaches to enhance CNN connectivity in the time domain, achieving notable performance improvements over traditional feature-based methods, while also examining the model's generalization capabilities in action recognition tasks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G228</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3125696988">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach to testing the null hypothesis of no difference in accuracy between two competing forecasts, utilizing a diverse range of measures and accommodating various types of forecast errors. It introduces asymptotic exact finite-sample tests that are evaluated and illustrated, advancing the field of predictive accuracy in statistics and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G229</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2559085405">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel method for real-time 2D pose estimation of multiple individuals in images using Part Affinity Fields (PAFs), which efficiently associates body parts with people while maintaining high accuracy. This approach, which combines global context encoding and a sequential prediction process, achieved top performance in the COCO 2016 keypoints challenge and surpassed previous benchmarks in the MPII Multi-Person dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G230</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2149298154">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive overview of statistical learning theory, tracing its evolution from a theoretical framework for function estimation in the 1960s to the development of practical algorithms like support vector machines in the 1990s, highlighting both its theoretical foundations and algorithmic applications in machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G231</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2153233077">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive survey of clustering algorithms used in data analysis across various fields, including statistics, computer science, and machine learning. It discusses the applications of these algorithms, highlights benchmark datasets, and explores related topics such as proximity measures and cluster validation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G232</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2257024953">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive guide to multivariate analysis using IBM SPSS 25, covering essential topics such as data measurement scales, statistical methods, data screening, validity testing, various regression techniques, and advanced analyses like factor and cluster analysis. Each chapter delves into specific analytical methods and their applications, making it a valuable resource for understanding and applying multivariate statistical techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G233</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2033403400">
      <data key="d1">This article presents objective criteria for evaluating clustering methods, addressing the challenges of interpreting results due to the absence of standardized metrics. It proposes specific performance aspects, such as the ability to retrieve inherent data structures and stability with new data, by analyzing the similarity between different clusterings of the same dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G234</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1983364832">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of a novel 3D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) designed for automated human action recognition in surveillance videos, which captures both spatial and temporal dimensions by processing multiple adjacent frames. The proposed model outperforms traditional methods by effectively combining predictions from various models and is tested in real-world environments, such as airport videos.</data>
      <data key="d2">G235</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1895577753">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a neural image caption generator that utilizes a deep recurrent architecture to automatically describe images, bridging the gap between computer vision and natural language processing. The model demonstrates significant improvements in accuracy and fluency over existing methods, achieving state-of-the-art BLEU scores on various datasets, including COCO and Flickr30k.</data>
      <data key="d2">G236</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2138122982">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of the &quot;multiple segment Viterbi&quot; (MSV) algorithm, an acceleration heuristic for profile hidden Markov models (HMMs) that significantly enhances the speed and efficiency of sequence database homology searches while maintaining sensitivity. Implemented in the HMMER3 package, the MSV algorithm allows for rapid evaluation of alignment scores and offers performance improvements of 100-1000 times over previous methods, making it a valuable tool for bioinformatics and data analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G237</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W6908809">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces ADADELTA, an adaptive learning rate method for gradient descent that adjusts per-dimension learning rates over time using first-order information, requiring no manual tuning and demonstrating robustness across various model architectures and data types. It showcases promising performance improvements on tasks such as MNIST digit classification and large-scale voice datasets in distributed environments.</data>
      <data key="d2">G238</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964043796">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a lightweight framework for deep reinforcement learning that employs asynchronous gradient descent optimization, demonstrating that parallel actor-learners enhance training stability. Notably, the best-performing variant, an actor-critic method, outperforms state-of-the-art results in Atari games and effectively addresses various continuous motor control tasks and navigation challenges in 3D environments using visual input.</data>
      <data key="d2">G239</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2048679005">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the co-training method, which effectively combines labeled and unlabeled data to enhance machine learning performance, particularly in the context of pattern recognition and data classification. It presents theoretical insights and practical implications for leveraging both types of data in unsupervised learning scenarios.</data>
      <data key="d2">G240</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2156406284">
      <data key="d1">The article presents the recognition-by-components (RBC) theory, which explains how humans perceive and recognize objects by segmenting images into simple geometric shapes called geons, based on five detectable properties. This theory highlights the robustness of object recognition across varying viewpoints and conditions, supported by experimental evidence demonstrating the rapid classification of occluded or altered images.</data>
      <data key="d2">G241</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1512098439">
      <data key="d1">This article introduces the Sequential Minimal Optimization (SMO) algorithm for efficiently training Support Vector Machines (SVMs) by breaking down large quadratic programming problems into smaller, analytically solvable tasks, significantly reducing computation time and memory usage compared to traditional methods. The SMO algorithm demonstrates remarkable speed improvements, particularly with sparse data sets, making it over 1000 times faster in certain applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G242</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963748441">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Stanford Question Answering Dataset (SQuAD), a comprehensive reading comprehension dataset featuring over 100,000 questions derived from Wikipedia articles, designed to advance machine comprehension research. It highlights the dataset's potential for improving automated reasoning and natural language processing, while noting the significant gap between machine performance and human accuracy, thus presenting a valuable challenge for future studies.</data>
      <data key="d2">G243</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2158899491">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a unified neural network architecture and learning algorithm designed for various natural language processing tasks, such as part-of-speech tagging and named entity recognition, by minimizing task-specific engineering and leveraging vast amounts of mostly unlabeled training data to learn internal representations. This approach aims to create an efficient tagging system with strong performance and minimal computational requirements.</data>
      <data key="d2">G244</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3005680577">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces SimCLR, a streamlined framework for contrastive learning of visual representations that enhances self-supervised learning without the need for specialized architectures or memory banks. It highlights key findings on the importance of data augmentations, learnable transformations, and the advantages of larger batch sizes, demonstrating significant improvements in performance on ImageNet compared to previous methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G245</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2149531726">
      <data key="d1">SeaView version 4 is a user-friendly, multiplatform software designed for molecular sequence alignment and phylogenetic tree construction, integrating features from previous versions and enhancing them with network database access and advanced algorithms like maximum-likelihood PhyML. This tool is particularly beneficial for teaching and occasional users in fields such as bioinformatics, evolutionary biology, and genomics, and is freely available for download.</data>
      <data key="d2">G246</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1825077972">
      <data key="d1">This book offers a comprehensive guide to neural network design, covering fundamental architectures, learning rules, and practical applications, with a focus on both feedforward and recurrent networks. It includes detailed examples, case studies, and downloadable software to enhance understanding and implementation of various neural network techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G247</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2088095316">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses practical methods for incorporating summary time-to-event data into meta-analysis, emphasizing the use of hazard ratios (HRs) in the absence of individual patient data. It highlights the need for greater awareness and adoption of these statistical techniques, which can enhance outcomes research and survival analysis in systematic reviews.</data>
      <data key="d2">G248</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1986280275">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the theory of reproducing kernels, covering various aspects such as the difference of reproducing kernels, product kernels, and their applications in mathematical optimization and machine learning. It also includes examples and specific cases, such as Bergman's and harmonic kernels, highlighting their significance in computational science and reproducible research.</data>
      <data key="d2">G249</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2161160262">
      <data key="d1">The article presents an efficient implementation of the k-means clustering algorithm, focusing on a new approach called filtering that utilizes kd-trees to optimize performance. It analyzes the algorithm's running time in relation to cluster separation and provides empirical evidence of its effectiveness through various applications, including color quantization and image segmentation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G250</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2135695572">
      <data key="d1">This article serves as a comprehensive guide to boosted regression trees (BRT), a powerful statistical modeling technique favored by ecologists for its ability to handle complex data features such as nonlinearity and interactions among predictors. It discusses the advantages of BRT over traditional models, provides practical insights through a case study on the short-finned eel, and includes a tutorial with code to assist ecologists in applying this method.</data>
      <data key="d2">G251</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2160719354">
      <data key="d1">&quot;Detection Theory: A User's Guide&quot; serves as both a practical manual and a theoretical overview of contemporary detection theory, highlighting recent advancements and exploring two primary alternative versions of the theory. It encompasses key topics such as pattern recognition, outlier detection, and machine vision, making it a valuable resource for researchers and practitioners in computer science and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G252</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2076879021">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses an improved scoring algorithm for the Implicit Association Test (IAT), evaluating various alternative procedures against traditional scoring methods. It highlights the new algorithm's superior performance in terms of correlation with self-report measures, resistance to response speed artifacts, internal consistency, and sensitivity to known influences.</data>
      <data key="d2">G253</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2156387975">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the advantages of deep sparse rectifier neural networks, highlighting their performance in training multi-layer networks despite the challenges posed by hard non-linearity and non-differentiability. It contrasts the effectiveness of logistic sigmoid and hyperbolic tangent neurons, ultimately demonstrating that rectified models can achieve comparable results in neural network performance.</data>
      <data key="d2">G254</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2151831732">
      <data key="d1">The article reviews recent advancements in profile hidden Markov models (profile HMMs), which transform multiple sequence alignments into position-specific scoring systems for identifying homologous sequences in databases. It highlights the effectiveness of profile HMMs in complementing traditional pairwise comparisons and discusses various software implementations that perform comparably to threading methods in protein structure prediction.</data>
      <data key="d2">G255</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2750384547">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Fashion-MNIST, a new dataset featuring 70,000 grayscale images of fashion products across 10 categories, designed as a direct replacement for the original MNIST dataset to benchmark machine learning algorithms. It provides the same image size and data structure, making it a valuable resource for researchers in image classification and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G256</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2109943925">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a practical guide to support vector classification, offering beginners a straightforward procedure to effectively implement support vector machines (SVM) and achieve satisfactory results in their classification tasks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G257</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2158275940">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a unified theoretical framework for combining classifiers that utilize different pattern representations, demonstrating that many existing combination methods are special cases of this framework. Through experimental comparisons, it finds that the sum rule, even under strict assumptions, outperforms other combination schemes, with theoretical justification provided through sensitivity analysis of estimation errors.</data>
      <data key="d2">G258</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2072128103">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the role of deep architectures in advancing artificial intelligence, emphasizing their necessity for learning complex functions and high-level abstractions in tasks like vision and language. It discusses recent developments in algorithms and architectures, particularly in the context of belief networks and unsupervised learning, while highlighting the challenges and future directions in this evolving field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G259</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1757796397">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a groundbreaking deep learning model that utilizes deep reinforcement learning to learn control policies directly from high-dimensional sensory input, specifically applied to seven Atari 2600 games. This convolutional neural network, trained with a variant of Q-learning, outperforms previous methods in six games and even surpasses human expert performance in three.</data>
      <data key="d2">G260</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2153663612">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to image denoising that utilizes sparse and redundant representations through learned dictionaries, specifically employing the K-SVD algorithm to effectively remove Gaussian noise from images. It explores two training methods and introduces a Bayesian framework to enhance the algorithm's performance, demonstrating state-of-the-art results that often exceed those of existing methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G261</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2970597249">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces XLNet, a generalized autoregressive pretraining method for language understanding that improves upon existing models like BERT by enabling bidirectional context learning and addressing pretrain-finetune discrepancies. By maximizing expected likelihood over all permutations of input sequences and integrating concepts from the Transformer-XL model, XLNet demonstrates superior performance across 20 language tasks, including question answering and sentiment analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G262</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2123504579">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses various aspects of data mining, including predictive analytics, machine learning, and pattern mining, while also exploring specialized areas such as educational data mining and data stream mining. It highlights the significance of these techniques in knowledge discovery and optimization within the broader field of data science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G263</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W179875071">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a recurrent neural network-based language model (RNN LM) that demonstrates significant improvements in speech recognition performance, achieving a 50% reduction in perplexity and lower word error rates compared to traditional backoff models. It highlights the advantages of connectionist approaches over standard n-gram techniques, despite the higher computational complexity involved in training.</data>
      <data key="d2">G264</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2026131661">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of an Extreme Learning Machine (ELM) framework that simplifies the implementation of least square support vector machines (LS-SVM) and proximal support vector machines (PSVM) for regression and multiclass classification tasks. It highlights ELM's advantages, including its ability to handle various feature mappings without extensive tuning, improved scalability, and faster performance compared to traditional SVM methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G265</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2476548250">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel convolutional neural network (CNN) architecture designed for real-time single image and video super-resolution, achieving significant improvements in reconstruction accuracy and computational efficiency. By introducing an efficient sub-pixel convolution layer, the proposed method enhances the upscaling process while reducing complexity, outperforming previous CNN-based approaches in both image and video quality.</data>
      <data key="d2">G266</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963372104">
      <data key="d1">The article presents Enhanced Deep Residual Networks (EDSR) for single image super-resolution, showcasing significant performance improvements over existing methods by optimizing network architecture and training stability. It also introduces a multi-scale system (MDSR) capable of reconstructing high-resolution images at various upscaling factors, demonstrating superior results in benchmark datasets and winning the NTIRE2017 Super-Resolution Challenge.</data>
      <data key="d2">G267</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2768348081">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces LightGBM, a highly efficient implementation of the Gradient Boosting Decision Tree (GBDT) algorithm, which addresses scalability issues in high-dimensional data through innovative techniques like Gradient-based One-Side Sampling (GOSS) and Exclusive Feature Bundling (EFB). These methods significantly enhance training speed—over 20 times faster than conventional approaches—while maintaining comparable accuracy on various public datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G268</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963857746">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Path Aggregation Network (PANet), a novel framework designed to enhance flow proposal-based instance segmentation by improving feature hierarchy and localization through bottom-up path augmentation. The proposed method achieves state-of-the-art results in the COCO 2017 Challenge for instance segmentation and object detection, demonstrating its effectiveness with minimal computational overhead.</data>
      <data key="d2">G269</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964199361">
      <data key="d1">The article examines the properties of neural machine translation using encoder-decoder models, specifically focusing on RNN Encoder-Decoder and gated recursive convolutional networks. It highlights the strengths and weaknesses of these models, noting their effectiveness with short sentences but a decline in performance with longer inputs, while also emphasizing the network's ability to automatically learn grammatical structures.</data>
      <data key="d2">G270</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2979826702">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Transformers: State-of-the-Art Natural Language Processing&quot; presents advancements in natural language processing (NLP) through the introduction and application of transformer models, highlighting their effectiveness in various NLP tasks and their significance in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence.</data>
      <data key="d2">G271</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3034999214">
      <data key="d1">The article presents BART, a novel approach to denoising sequence-to-sequence pre-training that enhances natural language generation, translation, and comprehension tasks. It explores the model's architecture and effectiveness in improving performance across various natural language processing applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G272</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4293580221">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the phenomenon of adversarial examples in machine learning, where small perturbations to input data lead to significant misclassifications by models, particularly neural networks. It argues that the primary cause of this vulnerability is the linear nature of these networks, and presents a new method for generating adversarial examples that can improve model training and reduce error rates, specifically demonstrated on the MNIST dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G273</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2008056655">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Support Vector Machines (SVMs) as a powerful machine learning technique, highlighting their theoretical advantages and real-world applications, such as text categorization and face detection. It features insights from experts, including practical implementation guidance and impressive results from various applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G274</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2519887557">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a scalable semi-supervised learning approach using graph convolutional networks, which efficiently process graph-structured data by leveraging localized spectral graph convolutions. The proposed model demonstrates significant performance improvements over existing methods in experiments conducted on citation knowledge datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G275</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W114517082">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of large-scale machine learning in the context of rapidly increasing data sizes and the limitations of traditional statistical methods, highlighting the effectiveness of stochastic gradient descent as a computationally efficient optimization algorithm that performs well even with large datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G276</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3194700752">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces YOLO (You Only Look Once), a novel approach to real-time object detection that frames the task as a regression problem, allowing a single neural network to predict bounding boxes and class probabilities directly from full images in one evaluation. YOLO achieves remarkable speed, processing 45 frames per second with the base model and 155 frames per second with a smaller version, while outperforming existing methods in generalization across various datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G277</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2604763608">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a model-agnostic meta-learning algorithm designed for rapid adaptation of deep networks across various learning tasks, enabling effective performance with minimal training samples. It highlights the method's ability to enhance generalization and fine-tuning, achieving state-of-the-art results in few-shot image classification benchmarks and improving the efficiency of neural network policy training.</data>
      <data key="d2">G278</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2955058313">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a Dual Attention Network (DANet) for scene segmentation, which enhances feature representation by integrating local and global contextual dependencies through self-attention mechanisms. The proposed method achieves state-of-the-art performance on several challenging datasets, including a Mean IoU score of 81.5% on the Cityscapes test set, without relying on coarse data.</data>
      <data key="d2">G279</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3101998545">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel multitask cascaded convolutional network framework for joint face detection and alignment in unconstrained environments, addressing challenges such as varying poses and occlusions. By leveraging a three-stage architecture and an online hard sample mining strategy, the proposed method demonstrates superior accuracy on benchmark datasets while maintaining real-time performance.</data>
      <data key="d2">G280</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2475287302">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to image style transfer using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) that effectively separates semantic content from artistic style, enabling the synthesis of new images that blend the characteristics of photographs with renowned artworks. It highlights the algorithm's potential for high-quality image manipulation and insights into deep learning applications in computer vision and multimedia retrieval.</data>
      <data key="d2">G281</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2110158442">
      <data key="d1">The article explores advanced algorithms for contour detection and hierarchical image segmentation in computer vision, presenting a framework that integrates multiple local cues through spectral clustering. It highlights the effectiveness of these methods, which allow for user interaction to refine segmentations, and demonstrates their superior performance compared to existing algorithms through extensive experimental evaluation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G282</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2912369344">
      <data key="d1">This article discusses a comprehensive book on multiuser detection techniques, highlighting its significance in communications technology. It serves as a resource for electrical engineering students and practicing engineers, offering foundational knowledge, advanced applications, and numerous exercises, while requiring only basic understanding of probability, linear algebra, and digital communications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G283</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2121058967">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel method for single-image super-resolution that utilizes sparse signal representation, leveraging over-complete dictionaries to effectively reconstruct high-resolution images from low-resolution inputs. By training dictionaries for low-resolution patches and enforcing similarity in their representations, the approach not only reduces computational costs but also enhances image quality, demonstrating robustness against noise and outperforming existing super-resolution techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G284</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2107473082">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses improvements made to the computer program Cervus, which enhances its ability to accommodate genotyping errors in paternity assignment, leading to increased accuracy in identifying parentage. The study demonstrates that the revised likelihood equations in version 3.0 of Cervus significantly improve success rates in paternity analysis, particularly in cases involving erroneous genotypes.</data>
      <data key="d2">G285</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1947481528">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the development of a novel recurrent convolutional network architecture designed for visual recognition and description tasks, emphasizing its ability to learn long-term dependencies and handle variable-length inputs and outputs. By integrating spatial and temporal processing, the model demonstrates significant improvements in benchmark video recognition and narration challenges compared to traditional methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G286</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2156303437">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the use of two-stream convolutional networks for action recognition in videos, focusing on integrating spatial and temporal information to enhance performance. It presents a novel architecture that leverages multi-frame dense optical flow and multi-task learning to improve classification accuracy on standard benchmarks, outperforming previous methods in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G287</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W10833075">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Yrjö Engeström's &quot;Learning by Expanding,&quot; which critiques traditional learning theories and introduces the concept of expansive activity as a framework for understanding learning as a transformative process in response to complex social changes. The second edition of this seminal text includes a new introduction that highlights the development and implementation of Engeström's ideas over time.</data>
      <data key="d2">G288</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963373786">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses innovative architectural features and training methods for generative adversarial networks (GANs), focusing on their applications in semi-supervised learning and generating visually realistic images. It highlights the achievement of state-of-the-art results in classification tasks and the generation of high-quality images, including MNIST samples that are indistinguishable from real ones, as confirmed by a visual Turing test.</data>
      <data key="d2">G289</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2601450892">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces prototypical networks as a solution for few-shot classification, enabling classifiers to generalize to unseen classes with minimal examples. It highlights the advantages of a simpler inductive bias in learning metric spaces, demonstrating significant performance improvements over complex meta-learning approaches, and achieving state-of-the-art results in zero-shot learning on the CU-Birds dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G290</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2174706414">
      <data key="d1">The article surveys a range of algorithms known as probabilistic topic models, which provide effective solutions for managing and analyzing large document archives, particularly in the context of disinformation detection and text mining within natural language processing. It highlights the intersection of probability theory, statistics, and machine learning in enhancing the understanding of document content.</data>
      <data key="d2">G291</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2123921160">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a generative method for face recognition that utilizes illumination cone models to effectively recognize faces under varying lighting and poses. By reconstructing shape albedo from a limited number of training images, the approach synthesizes novel poses and achieves high accuracy in identity assignment, even in challenging conditions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G292</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4298857966">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a groundbreaking deep learning model that utilizes deep reinforcement learning to develop control policies directly from high-dimensional sensory input, specifically applied to seven Atari 2600 games. This convolutional neural network, trained with a variant of Q-learning, outperforms previous methods and even surpasses human experts in three of the games.</data>
      <data key="d2">G293</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2253429366">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the advancements in computer-aided detection (CAD) using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), focusing on various CNN architectures, dataset characteristics, and the application of transfer learning. It evaluates the performance of different models in specific medical imaging tasks, such as lymph node detection and interstitial lung disease classification, and provides insights for improving CAD systems.</data>
      <data key="d2">G294</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962851944">
      <data key="d1">The article explores techniques for visualizing image classification models using deep Convolutional Networks, focusing on gradient-based methods to generate class-specific images and saliency maps. It highlights the application of these visualizations for weakly supervised object segmentation and connects gradient-based approaches to deconvolutional networks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G295</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2119387367">
      <data key="d1">This article reviews various feature selection techniques utilized in bioinformatics, highlighting their importance in machine learning and data mining applications. It provides a taxonomy of these techniques, discusses their applications, and explores both established and emerging methods in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G296</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2116064496">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a method for combining multiple latent-variable models, referred to as products of experts (PoE), to enhance rapid inference in perceptual systems while minimizing the challenges of sample generation. It highlights the use of contrastive divergence as an effective training objective to optimize the likelihood of these models, facilitating efficient parameter estimation despite the complexities introduced by the renormalization process.</data>
      <data key="d2">G297</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2103414828">
      <data key="d1">This article discusses a textbook from Prentice Hall's MATLAB Curriculum Series that explores the methodologies of neuro-fuzzy and soft computing, emphasizing both theoretical foundations and practical applications in the fields of computer science and artificial intelligence. It serves as a comprehensive resource for understanding machine learning and machine intelligence.</data>
      <data key="d2">G298</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2145094598">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach to constructing deep networks by stacking layers of denoising autoencoders, which are trained to remove noise from corrupted inputs. This method not only reduces classification errors compared to traditional autoencoders but also enhances the performance of subsequent classifiers, demonstrating the effectiveness of unsupervised learning in developing higher-level representations.</data>
      <data key="d2">G299</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2109887283">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a foundational overview of fixed-effect and random-effects models used in meta-analysis, highlighting their distinct assumptions and the importance of selecting the appropriate model for accurate statistical estimation and interpretation. It explains the key characteristics of each model and discusses factors to consider when choosing between them.</data>
      <data key="d2">G300</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964081807">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to neural network architecture design for scalable image recognition, focusing on learning transferable architectures that can be efficiently adapted from smaller datasets to larger ones. It introduces the &quot;NASNet space&quot; for architectural search and a regularization technique called ScheduledDropPath, achieving state-of-the-art accuracy on ImageNet while significantly reducing computational demands compared to traditional human-designed models.</data>
      <data key="d2">G301</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2325939864">
      <data key="d1">This article discusses advancements in deep face recognition, highlighting the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and large-scale training datasets to improve accuracy. It details the assembly of a comprehensive dataset and explores the complexities of current deep learning methods, achieving state-of-the-art results on established benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G302</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2155027007">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of using function approximation in reinforcement learning, particularly the limitations of traditional value function approaches. It introduces a novel method that utilizes policy gradient techniques, such as Williams's REINFORCE and actor-critic methods, to achieve a theoretically sound framework for estimating action-value or advantage functions, ultimately proving the convergence of locally optimal policies.</data>
      <data key="d2">G303</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2136848157">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the limitations of long short-term memory (LSTM) networks in processing continual input streams without resets, which can lead to performance degradation. It introduces a novel adaptive &quot;forget gate&quot; mechanism that allows the LSTM to reset its internal state at appropriate times, thereby improving its ability to handle sequential learning tasks and outperforming other recurrent neural network algorithms.</data>
      <data key="d2">G304</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2121512231">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces &quot;distruct,&quot; a software program designed for the graphical visualization of population structure by displaying individual membership coefficients in subpopulations through color-coded bars. It highlights the program's utility in analyzing multilocus genotypes and visualizing subpopulation assignment probabilities.</data>
      <data key="d2">G305</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2033419168">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the FERET evaluation methodology for face-recognition algorithms, highlighting the importance of a comprehensive facial image database and a structured testing procedure to assess and improve the performance of face-recognition systems. It details the establishment of the FERET program, which includes a database of over 14,000 images and aims to evaluate current technologies while identifying future research directions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G306</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2031614119">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the discrete cosine transform (DCT), detailing its definition, computation algorithm, and applications in digital processing, particularly in pattern recognition and Wiener filtering. It compares the performance of DCT with other orthogonal transforms, including the optimal Karhunen-Loève transform, in terms of rate-distortion criteria across various fields such as image analysis, computer vision, and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G307</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2336330109">
      <data key="d1">The Interactive Tree Of Life (iTOL) v3 is a redesigned online tool that allows users to display, manipulate, and annotate phylogenetic trees with enhanced features and support for various data types, accommodating trees with up to 100,000 leaves. It offers full interactive control for creating complex visualizations and simplifies tree management through a user-friendly account system, catering to a wide range of users in fields such as evolutionary biology and ecology.</data>
      <data key="d2">G308</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2119538357">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the concept of segmented assimilation in the context of the new second generation of immigrants in the United States, highlighting the unique challenges and diverse outcomes they face in adapting to American society compared to their parents and earlier immigrant groups. It presents empirical case studies and a typology of incorporation modes that illustrate the varying resources and vulnerabilities influencing their integration experiences.</data>
      <data key="d2">G309</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2132103241">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel kernel-based approach for object tracking that enhances target representation and localization of nonrigid objects through feature histogram regularization and spatial masking. By utilizing a Bhattacharyya coefficient-derived metric and mean shift optimization, the method effectively addresses challenges such as camera motion, occlusions, and scale variations, with potential applications in areas like face tracking and data association techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G310</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2002016471">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive tutorial on artificial neural networks (ANNs), exploring their development motivations, basic biological models, network architectures, and learning processes, while highlighting key ANN models and their successful application in character recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G311</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1782590233">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Labeled Faces in the Wild database, designed to facilitate research on face recognition in unconstrained environments, highlighting its diverse range of labeled photographs that reflect real-life variability in factors such as race, accessories, and occlusions. It also discusses experimental paradigms for consistent research and provides baseline results for state-of-the-art recognition systems.</data>
      <data key="d2">G312</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2140959843">
      <data key="d1">The article provides an overview of biometric recognition systems, which utilize physiological and behavioral characteristics to verify individual identities for secure access to various services, such as buildings and electronic devices. It discusses the advantages and limitations of biometrics, as well as associated privacy concerns.</data>
      <data key="d2">G313</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2105594594">
      <data key="d1">This article provides an introduction to hidden Markov models, highlighting their evolution from basic Markov chain theory to their recent applications in speech processing and other fields, driven by advancements in parameter optimization techniques. It aims to illustrate the significance and utility of these models in various domains, including machine learning and statistics.</data>
      <data key="d2">G314</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2015159529">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses scikit-image, a Python library for image processing that offers a range of algorithms and utilities for various applications in research, education, and industry. It highlights the library's advantages, real-world applications, and provides a link to the project homepage for further information.</data>
      <data key="d2">G315</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1485009520">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of a Convolutional LSTM (ConvLSTM) network for precipitation nowcasting, a machine learning approach aimed at predicting short-term rainfall intensity. It highlights the model's ability to effectively capture spatiotemporal correlations in weather data, outperforming traditional methods like the fully connected LSTM and the operational ROVER algorithm.</data>
      <data key="d2">G316</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2122759946">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive overview of the theory of point estimation, covering key concepts such as unbiasedness, equivariance, and optimality, while also exploring applications in fields like statistics, machine learning, and computer vision. It includes various tables, figures, and examples to illustrate the principles of estimation theory and its relevance to state estimation and object detection.</data>
      <data key="d2">G317</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2115012618">
      <data key="d1">The article presents an improved Bonferroni procedure for conducting multiple significance tests, aiming to enhance the accuracy and efficiency of statistical hypothesis testing in various fields, including biostatistics and experimental analysis. It discusses the methodology's advantages over traditional approaches, supported by numerical simulations and comparisons with existing methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G318</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3144619878">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Learning With Kernels&quot; explores the theoretical foundations and practical applications of kernel methods in machine learning, particularly focusing on support vector machines, regularization techniques, and optimization strategies within the context of supervised learning. It highlights the significance of these concepts in advancing computational learning theory and their impact on the field of computer science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G319</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964321699">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the extension of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to high-dimensional irregular domains represented by graphs, utilizing spectral graph theory to develop efficient localized filtering techniques. It demonstrates that this novel approach maintains linear computational complexity akin to traditional CNNs while effectively learning local and compositional features in various applications, as evidenced by experiments on datasets like MNIST and 20NEWS.</data>
      <data key="d2">G320</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1479807131">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive review of semi-supervised learning (SSL) in machine learning, exploring its algorithms, applications, and future research directions while highlighting its significance in utilizing unlabeled data for classification tasks across various domains such as images and text. It discusses key assumptions underlying SSL, presents a taxonomy of methods, and offers practical guidelines for practitioners based on extensive benchmark experiments.</data>
      <data key="d2">G321</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2605350416">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the application of deep neural networks to improve collaborative filtering in recommender systems, particularly focusing on techniques that address the challenges posed by implicit feedback. It highlights the potential of neural collaborative filtering to enhance recommendation accuracy and user experience.</data>
      <data key="d2">G322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2601564443">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Deformable Convolutional Networks, which enhance the transformation modeling capabilities of traditional convolutional neural networks (CNNs) by incorporating deformable convolution and RoI pooling modules that learn spatial sampling offsets from target tasks. This approach allows for improved performance in complex vision tasks like object detection and semantic segmentation, and the methods can be easily integrated into existing CNN architectures.</data>
      <data key="d2">G323</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3034971973">
      <data key="d1">The article presents EfficientDet, a new family of object detection models that enhance efficiency through innovative architectural optimizations, including a weighted bi-directional feature pyramid and a compound scaling method. These advancements enable EfficientDet to achieve state-of-the-art performance with significantly fewer parameters and computational resources compared to previous models.</data>
      <data key="d2">G324</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2060806362">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a straightforward Lagrangian multiplier test for detecting heteroscedasticity in linear regression models, utilizing ordinary least squares (OLS) residuals for computation. It also includes finite sample evidence to support the asymptotic properties of the test, highlighting its relevance in fields such as financial econometrics and data science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G325</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2110798204">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the advantages of deep neural networks over shallow architectures in terms of efficiency and representation capabilities, highlighting the challenges of training such networks. It focuses on the greedy layer-wise unsupervised learning algorithm introduced by Hinton et al. for training deep belief networks, exploring its effectiveness in optimizing weight initialization and enhancing generalization through internal representations.</data>
      <data key="d2">G326</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1905882502">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a model that generates natural language descriptions of images by leveraging deep visual-semantic alignments, utilizing a combination of Convolutional Neural Networks and bidirectional Recurrent Neural Networks to establish inter-modal correspondences. The proposed multimodal network architecture demonstrates state-of-the-art performance in image retrieval tasks across several datasets, including Flickr8K, Flickr30K, and MSCOCO, significantly outperforming existing baselines.</data>
      <data key="d2">G327</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964241181">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Cascade R-CNN, a multi-stage object detection architecture designed to improve detection quality by addressing issues related to intersection over union (IoU) thresholds and overfitting. By employing a sequence of increasingly selective detectors, Cascade R-CNN enhances performance on challenging datasets like COCO, demonstrating its effectiveness across various architectures.</data>
      <data key="d2">G328</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964059111">
      <data key="d1">The article explores how dropout training in deep neural networks can be interpreted as a Bayesian approximation to effectively represent model uncertainty in machine learning. By leveraging this approach, the authors demonstrate significant improvements in predictive performance and uncertainty quantification across various network architectures and classification tasks, particularly using the MNIST dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G329</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964299589">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a method called deep compression, which combines pruning, trained quantization, and Huffman coding to significantly reduce the storage requirements of deep neural networks by up to 49 times without compromising accuracy. This approach enables efficient deployment of neural networks on resource-constrained embedded systems and enhances performance in mobile applications by improving speed and energy efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d2">G330</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4230206799">
      <data key="d1">This article explores likelihood-based inference in cointegrated vector autoregressive models, focusing on the statistical analysis of non-stationary multivariate time series. It discusses key concepts such as cointegration, common trends, and presents results including the derivation of the trace test for cointegrating rank and the asymptotic distributions of adjustment coefficients.</data>
      <data key="d2">G331</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1576520375">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of training support vector machines (SVMs) for large-scale datasets, highlighting the quadratic optimization problem involved and the memory and time constraints of traditional methods. It presents algorithmic advancements from version 2.0 that enhance the practicality of large-scale SVM learning and offers guidelines for applying SVMs in various domains.</data>
      <data key="d2">G332</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963420272">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Context Encoders, an unsupervised visual feature learning algorithm that utilizes context-based pixel prediction to inpaint missing regions in images. By training a convolutional neural network to generate content based on surrounding pixels, the method enhances feature representation for various tasks, including classification, detection, and segmentation, while demonstrating improved results through the use of adversarial loss.</data>
      <data key="d2">G333</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2911489562">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces BioBERT, a pre-trained biomedical language representation model designed to enhance biomedical text mining by adapting the BERT architecture for domain-specific applications. It demonstrates significant performance improvements over previous models in tasks such as named entity recognition, relation extraction, and question answering, while also providing access to the model and fine-tuning code for further research.</data>
      <data key="d2">G334</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2131241448">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the use of Bayesian optimization to automate the tuning of hyperparameters in machine learning algorithms, highlighting its effectiveness in improving performance beyond expert-level results. It emphasizes the role of Gaussian processes in efficiently utilizing information from previous experiments and introduces methods for optimizing variable costs and leveraging parallel experimentation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G335</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2969985801">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces ArcFace, a novel Additive Angular Margin Loss designed to enhance the discriminative power of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks for large-scale face recognition. It provides a comprehensive evaluation against state-of-the-art methods, demonstrating superior performance across multiple benchmarks while maintaining low computational overhead, and offers the code for future research.</data>
      <data key="d2">G336</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2593414223">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Least Squares Generative Adversarial Networks (LSGANs) as an improvement over traditional GANs, addressing the vanishing gradients problem by using a least squares loss function for the discriminator. It highlights the advantages of LSGANs, including the generation of higher quality images and improved stability in evaluations on datasets like LSUN and CIFAR-10.</data>
      <data key="d2">G337</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2243397390">
      <data key="d1">The article presents the DeepFool algorithm, a novel method designed to effectively generate small perturbations that can deceive state-of-the-art deep neural networks in image classification tasks, thereby providing a reliable way to assess the robustness of these classifiers against adversarial attacks. Through extensive experiments, the authors demonstrate that DeepFool outperforms existing techniques in quantifying the vulnerability of deep learning models.</data>
      <data key="d2">G338</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1601740268">
      <data key="d1">This book serves as a comprehensive introduction to Support Vector Machines (SVMs), detailing their theoretical foundations and practical applications in various fields such as text categorization and image classification. It offers a gradual and accessible approach to understanding SVMs and related techniques, making it suitable for both students and practitioners in machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G339</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2395579298">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive survey of transfer learning, a machine learning methodology that enables the development of high-performance models by leveraging knowledge from different domains, particularly in scenarios where data collection is challenging. It defines transfer learning, reviews current solutions and applications, and discusses future research directions, along with providing resources for software downloads related to the topic.</data>
      <data key="d2">G340</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1625255723">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel method for visual categorization that utilizes bags of keypoints based on vector quantization of affine invariant descriptors from image patches. It evaluates two classifier implementations, Naive Bayes and SVM, demonstrating that the approach achieves robust categorization across seven semantic categories, effectively handling background clutter without relying on geometric information.</data>
      <data key="d2">G341</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2470673105">
      <data key="d1">The article presents Hierarchical Attention Networks (HANs) as a novel approach for document classification, leveraging deep learning techniques to improve the accuracy and efficiency of automatic classification in text mining and information fusion tasks. The authors discuss the architecture and benefits of HANs in handling hierarchical structures in documents, contributing to advancements in machine learning and computational intelligence.</data>
      <data key="d2">G342</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2009086942">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses advancements in statistical pattern recognition and machine learning, highlighting their applications in various fields such as data science and image analysis, with a focus on both supervised and unsupervised learning techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G343</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2335728318">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of detecting and reading digits in natural images, particularly in street-level photographs, and presents a new benchmark dataset of over 600,000 labeled images to facilitate research in this area. It explores the limitations of existing methods using hand-designed features and demonstrates the effectiveness of unsupervised feature learning techniques in improving digit recognition performance.</data>
      <data key="d2">G344</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2144673831">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the MCMCglmm R package, which utilizes Markov chain Monte Carlo methods to fit multi-response generalized linear mixed models for non-Gaussian data. It highlights the package's capabilities in handling various response distributions, random effects, and missing data, while emphasizing its implementation in C/C++ for efficient computation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G345</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2171277043">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel network architecture utilizing locally-tuned processing units for efficient learning in classification and function approximation tasks, advocating a hybrid learning approach that combines supervised and self-organized methods. This architecture offers faster training than traditional backpropagation by leveraging local representations and linear rules, making it suitable for real-time data analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G346</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2149723649">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a General Regression Neural Network (GRNN), a memory-based network that estimates continuous variables and effectively models both linear and nonlinear regression surfaces, even with sparse multidimensional data. It highlights the GRNN's one-pass learning algorithm and its applicability to various problems where linearity assumptions may not hold.</data>
      <data key="d2">G347</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2125213524">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a modified version of the particle swarm algorithm designed to operate with discrete binary variables, shifting from its traditional continuous space application. It discusses the algorithm's mechanics, including the probability of binary outcomes, and explores various examples, applications, and challenges associated with this adaptation in fields such as machine learning and combinatorial optimization.</data>
      <data key="d2">G348</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2979750740">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach called Dynamic Graph CNN, which enhances the learning capabilities of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on point clouds by incorporating topological information through dynamically computed graphs. This method aims to improve high-level tasks such as classification and segmentation in 3D data analysis, demonstrating superior performance on standard benchmarks like ModelNet40 and ShapeNetPart.</data>
      <data key="d2">G349</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2949650786">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a residual learning framework that simplifies the training of significantly deeper neural networks, demonstrating its effectiveness through empirical results on the ImageNet dataset, where a model with 152 layers achieved a 3.57% error rate, winning first place in the ILSVRC 2015 classification task. It highlights the importance of deep representations in visual recognition tasks, showing substantial improvements in object detection performance on the COCO dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G350</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2106053110">
      <data key="d1">This article presents a method for learning a Mahalanobis distance for k-nearest neighbor (kNN) classification, emphasizing the importance of distance metrics in achieving accurate classification. The proposed approach utilizes a global linear transformation of the input space to maximize class separation while maintaining a large margin, leading to significant improvements in classification accuracy across various datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G351</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2016589492">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a gradient-following learning algorithm specifically designed for continually running fully recurrent neural networks, highlighting its ability to operate without defined training intervals while addressing the challenges of nonlocal communication and computational expense in learning complex tasks over varying time periods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G352</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2111286455">
      <data key="d1">The article critiques traditional statistical methods for evaluating geographic models, particularly the inadequacy of the correlation coefficient and its significance tests, and proposes alternative measures such as root mean squared error (RMSE) and a new index of agreement (d) for more effective model validation. It highlights the growing prevalence of digital algorithms and data plots in the field, emphasizing the need for improved validation techniques in model-based reasoning and data science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G353</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2099213660">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a feasibility study on Feature-Oriented Domain Analysis (FODA), emphasizing the importance of systematic software reuse through the identification of commonalities in related systems. It outlines methods for describing product processes and illustrates their application using a window management system as a case study.</data>
      <data key="d2">G354</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2135293965">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses various methods to enhance the performance and training of neural network classifiers, highlighting the use of cross-validation for optimizing network architecture and demonstrating that ensemble techniques can effectively reduce residual generalization error.</data>
      <data key="d2">G355</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2950094539">
      <data key="d1">Caffe is a powerful C++ library with Python and MATLAB bindings designed for efficient training and deployment of convolutional neural networks and other deep learning models, catering to multimedia scientists and practitioners. It supports high-performance GPU computation, enabling the processing of millions of images daily, while facilitating experimentation and development across various platforms through its modular architecture.</data>
      <data key="d2">G356</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2133564696">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to neural machine translation that enhances the traditional encoder-decoder architecture by incorporating a mechanism for soft alignment, allowing the model to automatically identify relevant parts of the source sentence when predicting target words. This method achieves performance comparable to state-of-the-art phrase-based systems in English-to-French translation, while also providing intuitive alignment insights.</data>
      <data key="d2">G357</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2523246573">
      <data key="d1">This article provides an overview of gradient descent optimization algorithms, highlighting their strengths and weaknesses while offering insights into their behavior and practical applications. It covers various variants of gradient descent, challenges faced, common architectures in parallel distributed settings, and additional strategies for optimization.</data>
      <data key="d2">G358</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2746553466">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the limitations of the Q-learning algorithm, particularly its tendency to overestimate action values, and demonstrates that this issue negatively impacts performance in deep reinforcement learning applications like the DQN algorithm. It introduces Double Q-Learning as a solution that not only mitigates these overestimations but also enhances performance across various Atari 2600 games.</data>
      <data key="d2">G359</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2914874661">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the 2016 ACM SIGKDD International Conference on Knowledge Discovery and Data Mining (KDD'16), highlighting its role as a premier forum for presenting cutting-edge research and real-world applications in data science and machine learning. It emphasizes the conference's focus on fostering collaboration between researchers, practitioners, and industry leaders to drive innovation and address emerging technology trends in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G360</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2138621090">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel method for dimensionality reduction called Reduction by Learning an Invariant Mapping (DrLIM), which effectively maps high-dimensional data to a lower-dimensional manifold by preserving neighborhood relationships without relying on distance measures. The method demonstrates its ability to learn invariant mappings under certain transformations, showcasing its effectiveness through various experiments and comparisons with other techniques like Locally Linear Embedding (LLE).</data>
      <data key="d2">G361</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2745461083">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel combined bottom-up and top-down attention mechanism for image captioning and visual question answering (VQA), which enhances understanding through detailed analysis of objects and salient regions. This approach, based on Faster R-CNN, achieves state-of-the-art results on the MSCOCO test server and secures first place in the 2017 VQA Challenge, demonstrating its effectiveness in both tasks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G362</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2296283641">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Neural Architectures for Named Entity Recognition&quot; by Lample et al. explores innovative neural network architectures designed to enhance the performance of named entity recognition (NER) tasks in natural language processing, highlighting advancements in deep learning and machine learning techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G363</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2593768305">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to adversarial discriminative domain adaptation, introducing a generalized framework that integrates modeling, untied weight sharing, and GAN loss, termed Discriminative Domain Adaptation (ADDA). This method aims to enhance generalization performance in the presence of domain shifts, demonstrating superior effectiveness and simplicity compared to existing domain-adversarial techniques in challenging cross-modality object classification tasks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G364</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2982770724">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces FCOS, a fully convolutional one-stage object detector that operates without pre-defined anchor boxes, simplifying the object detection process by eliminating complex computations and hyper-parameters. Achieving a significant accuracy improvement with a simpler framework, FCOS demonstrates its potential as a strong alternative for various instance-level tasks in computer vision.</data>
      <data key="d2">G365</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1974116356">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the Blast2GO suite, a bioinformatics tool designed for high-throughput functional annotation of DNA and protein sequences, which facilitates the analysis and interpretation of large genomic datasets through automated Gene Ontology vocabulary integration and user-friendly visualization features. It highlights the suite's capabilities in managing and analyzing data, making it a valuable resource for biologists engaged in functional genomics research.</data>
      <data key="d2">G366</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1985258161">
      <data key="d1">The article provides an overview of nonparametric regression techniques, specifically focusing on kernel and nearest-neighbor methods, which allow for curve estimation without strong assumptions about the underlying function. It highlights their utility in building and validating parametric models, as well as in data description, making these methods accessible for beginners and practitioners in statistics and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G367</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2136396015">
      <data key="d1">The article reviews various image denoising algorithms, highlighting their limitations in practical applications, and introduces a new nonlocal means (NL-means) method that effectively preserves the structure of digital images while minimizing artifacts. It employs a comprehensive mathematical and experimental methodology to compare classical approaches and demonstrates the NL-means' asymptotic optimality under generic statistical models.</data>
      <data key="d2">G368</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2125186487">
      <data key="d1">&quot;Computer Vision: Algorithms and Applications&quot; is a comprehensive textbook that explores the challenges and techniques in computer vision, detailing algorithms for image analysis and their real-world applications, from medical imaging to consumer-level tasks. It emphasizes a scientific approach to understanding imaging processes, includes project-oriented exercises, and serves as a valuable resource for upper-level undergraduate and graduate students in science and engineering.</data>
      <data key="d2">G369</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2115403315">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel method called Transfer Component Analysis (TCA) for domain adaptation, which facilitates the transfer of knowledge from a source domain to a related target domain by discovering effective feature representations. TCA utilizes maximum mean discrepancy in a reproducing kernel Hilbert space to preserve data properties and enhance classifier training, while also extending to a semi-supervised setting to uncover hidden relationships between labels across domains.</data>
      <data key="d2">G370</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2115462905">
      <data key="d1">ConsensusClusterPlus is an open-source R package designed for unsupervised class discovery in cancer research, utilizing consensus clustering to provide quantitative stability assessments and enhanced visualizations, including item tracking and consensus plots. This tool aids researchers in identifying intrinsic biological groups within datasets, facilitating more informed decision-making in their analyses.</data>
      <data key="d2">G371</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1930624869">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the concept of random decision forests, highlighting their advantages over traditional decision trees in terms of execution speed and generalization accuracy. It proposes a method for constructing tree-based models that can expand their capacity by utilizing multiple randomly selected subspaces of the feature space, demonstrating improved classification performance through experiments on handwritten digit recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G372</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2062118960">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the effectiveness of generic descriptors from convolutional neural networks, specifically the OverFeat network, in various recognition tasks, demonstrating that these features can outperform highly tuned state-of-the-art systems across multiple datasets. The findings suggest that deep learning models should be prioritized for tasks involving image analysis and recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G373</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2137226992">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Support Vector Regression (SVR), a novel regression technique inspired by Vapnik's support vector concept, and compares its performance against committee trees and ridge regression in feature space. The findings suggest that SVR may offer advantages in high-dimensional spaces due to its optimization independence from input dimensions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G374</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4299828299">
      <data key="d1">The article serves as an index for the papers presented at the 29th International Conference on Machine Learning (ICML-12), held in Edinburgh, Scotland, from June 27 to July 3, 2012, covering a wide range of topics in machine learning, including supervised and unsupervised learning, deep learning, and data science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G375</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W82038529">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a study on the factors influencing the internationalization of firms, focusing on variables such as firm size, founders' international experience, and technology intensity. It employs multivariate data analysis techniques, including regression models and logarithmic transformations, to assess the relationships between these factors and the firms' performance, while ensuring construct validity through statistical measures.</data>
      <data key="d2">G376</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3146306708">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel unsupervised learning algorithm designed to classify reviews as either recommended or not based on the semantic orientation of phrases containing adjectives and adverbs. By analyzing the average sentiment of these phrases, the algorithm achieves a classification accuracy of 74% across various domains, with performance varying from 84% for automobile reviews to 66% for movie reviews.</data>
      <data key="d2">G377</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963826681">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach to unsupervised domain adaptation using backpropagation, which enables deep learning models to effectively learn from large amounts of source data while adapting to unlabeled target domains. By incorporating a gradient reversal layer into standard feed-forward architectures, the method enhances the emergence of discriminative features that are invariant to domain shifts, achieving superior performance in image classification tasks compared to previous state-of-the-art methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G378</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2996428491">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces ALBERT, a lightweight version of BERT designed to enhance the efficiency of self-supervised learning for language representations by employing parameter-reduction techniques and a self-supervised loss that improves inter-sentence coherence, achieving state-of-the-art results on various benchmarks while using fewer parameters than BERT-large.</data>
      <data key="d2">G379</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2949888546">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel end-to-end approach for sequence-to-sequence learning using Deep Neural Networks, specifically employing multilayered Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks to translate between English and French. The method demonstrates significant performance improvements, achieving a BLEU score of 34.8 on the WMT'14 dataset, surpassing traditional phrase-based systems and effectively handling long sentences and word order variations.</data>
      <data key="d2">G380</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3141830910">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive analysis of cointegrated vector autoregressive models, emphasizing their ability to capture both short-run dynamics and long-run equilibrium in non-stationary time series. It serves as a resource for graduate students and researchers, offering practical techniques for statistical inference and estimation using Gaussian likelihood functions, along with exercises and empirical examples.</data>
      <data key="d2">G381</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2019111214">
      <data key="d1">This article presents a theoretical model for understanding face recognition, outlining seven distinct types of information derived from faces and exploring the cognitive processes involved in recognizing familiar faces. It integrates findings from various studies, including laboratory experiments and observations of individuals with cerebral injuries, to clarify the similarities and differences between face recognition and other forms of recognition, such as object and word recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G382</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2115309705">
      <data key="d1">The article provides an overview of SPIN, an efficient model checker used for verifying distributed software systems, highlighting its theoretical foundations and practical applications in detecting design errors across various domains, including telecommunications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G383</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2143908786">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the RPROP (resilient propagation) algorithm, a direct adaptive method designed to enhance the speed of backpropagation learning in multilayer feedforward networks by optimizing weight updates based solely on the sign of the error function's derivative, thereby improving efficiency and clarity compared to traditional gradient-descent methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G384</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2473418344">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses advancements in deep learning techniques that incorporate differential privacy to protect sensitive information in large datasets used for training neural networks. It highlights the development of new algorithms that effectively analyze privacy costs while maintaining model quality and efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d2">G385</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3198350258">
      <data key="d1">The article explores two machine learning techniques applied to the game of checkers, demonstrating that a computer can learn to play at a higher level than its programmer within just 8 to 10 hours of gameplay, using only the game's rules and a set of parameters. The findings highlight the broader applicability of these machine learning principles beyond checkers.</data>
      <data key="d2">G386</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4297814571">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the intriguing properties of deep neural networks, highlighting their expressiveness and state-of-the-art performance in tasks like speech and visual recognition, while also revealing their tendency to produce uninterpretable solutions and exhibit discontinuous input-output mappings that can lead to misclassifications through imperceptible perturbations.</data>
      <data key="d2">G387</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2997574889">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a novel approach to constructing deep networks by stacking layers of denoising autoencoders, which are trained to remove noise from corrupted input data, thereby facilitating the learning of useful representations in deep learning applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G388</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2139086914">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the application of random forests (RF) as a powerful classification tool in ecology, highlighting its advantages such as high accuracy, variable importance assessment, and flexibility in data analysis. It presents case studies on invasive plant species, rare lichens, and nesting sites of cavity-nesting birds, demonstrating RF's effectiveness compared to traditional classification methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G389</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2136251662">
      <data key="d1">This article explores the classification of hyperspectral remote sensing images using support vector machines (SVMs), providing a theoretical and experimental analysis of SVMs in high-dimensional feature spaces. It compares the effectiveness of SVMs against conventional feature-reduction methods and other classifiers, while also examining various strategies for addressing binary and multiclass classification problems.</data>
      <data key="d2">G390</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2274287116">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the advancements in image recognition performance through the development of Inception-v4 and Inception-ResNet architectures, highlighting the significant impact of residual connections on training efficiency and accuracy. It presents empirical evidence of improved performance and introduces new streamlined architectures that enhance classification tasks, ultimately achieving a top-5 error rate of 3.08 percent on the ImageNet challenge.</data>
      <data key="d2">G391</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2140952049">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces FIMO, a software tool designed for scanning DNA or protein sequences to identify occurrences of specific motifs using position-specific frequency matrices. It details the program's methodology, including its scoring system and output formats, and highlights its efficiency and availability as part of the MEME Suite toolkit.</data>
      <data key="d2">G392</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4294558607">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses GraphSAGE, an inductive framework for generating low-dimensional embeddings of nodes in large graphs, which allows for effective prediction tasks without requiring the entire graph during training. By leveraging node feature information and aggregating local neighborhood features, GraphSAGE demonstrates superior performance on various node-classification benchmarks, including citation and protein-protein interaction datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G393</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2137344397">
      <data key="d1">This article discusses mixed multinomial logit (MMNL) models for discrete response, demonstrating that these models can closely approximate any choice model derived from utility maximization. It highlights practical estimation methods, including Maximum Simulated Likelihood Estimation, and applies the approach to analyze demand for alternative vehicles, showcasing its computational efficiency and flexibility.</data>
      <data key="d2">G394</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2998508934">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel family of adaptive subgradient methods designed for online learning and stochastic optimization, which leverage insights from previously observed data to enhance gradient-based learning efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d2">G395</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1873332500">
      <data key="d1">This article provides an overview of various classification techniques in supervised machine learning, focusing on how these methods build models to predict class labels based on predictor features. It aims to guide researchers by highlighting key theoretical issues and suggesting potential research directions in the field of machine learning and data classification.</data>
      <data key="d2">G396</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963800363">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel method for generating high-resolution, photo-realistic images from semantic label maps using conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs), achieving 2048 × 1024 resolution and enhanced realism through innovative loss functions and multi-scale architectures. Additionally, it introduces interactive visual manipulation features, allowing users to edit images by adding or removing objects and altering their appearance, significantly improving upon existing image synthesis and editing techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G397</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2140310134">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Bayesian Personalized Ranking (BPR) as a method for item recommendation based on implicit feedback, such as clicks and purchases. It introduces a new optimization criterion, BPR-Opt, which directly optimizes ranking through Bayesian analysis, and presents a learning algorithm that utilizes stochastic gradient descent to enhance the performance of recommender models like matrix factorization and k-nearest neighbors.</data>
      <data key="d2">G398</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3034552520">
      <data key="d1">The article presents the Efficient Channel Attention (ECA) module, a novel approach designed to enhance the performance of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) while minimizing model complexity. By avoiding dimensionality reduction and employing a local strategy with adaptive kernel size convolution, ECA demonstrates significant improvements in accuracy and efficiency across various tasks, including image classification and object detection, compared to existing methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G399</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2105464873">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the concept of sparse coding in the mammalian striate cortex, particularly focusing on how simple cells utilize an overcomplete basis set to produce sparse output responses to natural images. It discusses the neurobiological implications of this coding strategy, highlighting how non-orthogonal basis functions can lead to non-linear input-output relationships and predict interactions among neural units in response to complex stimuli.</data>
      <data key="d2">G400</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1496317909">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Least Squares Support Vector Machines (LS-SVM), covering fundamental methods, Bayesian inference for LS-SVM models, and their robustness in large-scale problems. It also explores applications in unsupervised learning and recurrent networks, highlighting their relevance in statistical learning theory and machine learning within computer science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G401</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964105864">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Relation Network (RN), a novel framework for few-shot learning that enables classifiers to recognize new classes with minimal examples by learning deep distance metrics through meta-learning. The RN is trained end-to-end and can classify new instances by computing relation scores without further network updates, demonstrating improved performance in both few-shot and zero-shot learning tasks across multiple benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G402</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963981733">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel two time-scale update rule (TTUR) for training Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), demonstrating that this approach can converge to a local Nash equilibrium under certain conditions. It also highlights the effectiveness of TTUR in improving image generation performance, as evidenced by superior results on various benchmark datasets compared to traditional methods.</data>
      <data key="d2">G403</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4300939921">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the advancements in image recognition through deep convolutional networks, specifically focusing on the Inception-v4 and Inception-ResNet architectures. It highlights the benefits of incorporating residual connections, which significantly accelerate training and improve performance, ultimately achieving a top-5 error rate of 3.08% on the ImageNet challenge.</data>
      <data key="d2">G404</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2964253222">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and presents a robust optimization approach to enhance the resilience of these models. It emphasizes the importance of defining specific classes of adversaries to develop training methods that significantly improve resistance to a wide range of attacks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G405</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2116148865">
      <data key="d1">The article explores advancements in using the greedy algorithm orthogonal matching pursuit (OMP) for solving the sparse approximation problem with redundant dictionaries, establishing conditions for optimal signal representation and introducing a cumulative coherence function to measure incoherence. It also discusses the identification of nonsparse atoms in dictionaries and demonstrates that the algorithm can achieve approximations with only a small error compared to the best possible representation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G406</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2204750386">
      <data key="d1">The article presents the &quot;Market-1501&quot; dataset, a comprehensive resource for person re-identification that addresses limitations of existing datasets by offering over 32,000 annotated images and a large distractor set, all captured in a multi-camera environment. Additionally, it introduces an unsupervised Bag-of-Words descriptor for improved accuracy in re-identification tasks, demonstrating its effectiveness on various benchmark datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1990381576">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the use of Generalized Cross-Validation (GCV) as a method for selecting an optimal ridge parameter (λ) in regression models, highlighting its advantages over traditional cross-validation techniques by not requiring knowledge of the error variance and its applicability in scenarios with limited data. It also explores the integration of GCV with subset selection and singular truncation methods in regression analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G408</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2128017662">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a scalable recognition scheme utilizing a vocabulary tree to efficiently identify a large number of objects, demonstrated through the recognition of CD covers from a database of 40,000 images. By hierarchically quantizing local region descriptors, the approach significantly enhances retrieval quality and can be applied to datasets as large as one million images.</data>
      <data key="d2">G409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1745334888">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel semantic segmentation algorithm that utilizes a deep deconvolution network built on VGG's 16-layer architecture, enhancing pixelwise class label predictions through unpooling layers. This method effectively addresses the limitations of existing techniques by integrating proposal-wise predictions, achieving superior accuracy on the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset without relying on the Microsoft COCO dataset.</data>
      <data key="d2">G410</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4386076325">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses YOLOv7, a groundbreaking real-time object detection model that introduces a trainable bag-of-freebies approach, achieving a new state-of-the-art performance with a remarkable 56.8% average precision and speeds ranging from 5 to 120 frames per second. It highlights the model's innovative architecture and training methods, emphasizing its superiority over existing detectors and providing access to the source code for further research and development.</data>
      <data key="d2">G411</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2217896605">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a neural network-based system for detecting upright frontal faces in images, utilizing a retinally connected network to analyze image windows and improve accuracy through multiple network arbitration and a bootstrap algorithm for negative example collection. Comparisons with other advanced systems demonstrate that this approach achieves competitive false-positive rates in face detection.</data>
      <data key="d2">G412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2891503716">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive survey on Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI), highlighting the challenges of transparency in AI systems and the importance of developing explainable models to foster trust and understanding. It reviews existing approaches, discusses current trends, and outlines future directions in the rapidly evolving field of XAI.</data>
      <data key="d2">G413</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2997617958">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a unified neural network architecture and learning algorithm designed for a range of natural language processing tasks, such as part-of-speech tagging, chunking, and named entity recognition, highlighting its versatility and effectiveness in the field of computational linguistics.</data>
      <data key="d2">G414</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2912213068">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of isolated data and privacy in artificial intelligence, proposing a comprehensive framework for secure federated learning that enhances collaboration among organizations while protecting user privacy. It expands on the original federated learning model introduced by Google in 2016, detailing various learning types, architectures, and applications in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G415</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2916798096">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach to human pose estimation that emphasizes learning high-resolution representations throughout the entire process, rather than relying on low-resolution outputs. The proposed network architecture incorporates multi-resolution parallel connections and repeated multi-scale fusions, resulting in more accurate keypoint predictions, as demonstrated on benchmark datasets like COCO and MPII.</data>
      <data key="d2">G416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2082179468">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Incremental Dynamic Analysis (IDA), a parametric method for evaluating structural performance under seismic loads by scaling ground motion records to various intensity levels. It presents a unified framework for IDA, including terminology, algorithms, and properties for both single and multi-degree-of-freedom structures, while also exploring its application in performance-based earthquake engineering.</data>
      <data key="d2">G417</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2103943262">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Extended Cohn-Kanade Dataset (CK+), an enhanced version of the original CK database designed to improve the automatic detection of facial expressions by addressing previous limitations, such as the validation of emotion labels and the lack of standardized evaluation metrics. It details the dataset's expansion, including a 22% increase in subject sequences and the addition of non-posed smiles, while also providing baseline results for algorithm performance using advanced machine learning techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G418</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2553303224">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a method for Neural Architecture Search using reinforcement learning, where a recurrent network generates model descriptions to optimize neural network architectures. The proposed approach achieves state-of-the-art performance on the CIFAR-10 dataset, surpassing human-designed architectures and demonstrating superior results in tasks like character modeling on the Penn Treebank.</data>
      <data key="d2">G419</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2102544846">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces a novel technique called two-dimensional principal component analysis (2DPCA) for face representation and recognition, which utilizes 2D matrices for feature extraction without the need for vector transformation. Experimental results demonstrate that 2DPCA achieves higher recognition rates and greater computational efficiency compared to traditional PCA across multiple face databases.</data>
      <data key="d2">G420</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2950967305">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Gctf, a GPU-accelerated program designed for real-time determination and correction of the contrast transfer function (CTF) in cryo-electron microscopy, emphasizing its speed and accuracy improvements through innovative techniques and its compatibility with other cryoEM software. It highlights the program's ability to refine local defocus for individual particles, enhancing subsequent image processing and providing robust results across various datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G421</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2142194269">
      <data key="d1">This article explores the recognition of realistic human actions in videos, particularly using movie scripts for automatic annotation to overcome the lack of annotated datasets. It presents a novel method that enhances action classification through advanced machine learning techniques, achieving significant accuracy improvements on standard datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G422</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2134603844">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the Extreme Learning Machine (ELM) algorithm, a novel approach to training feedforward neural networks that significantly accelerates learning speed by randomly selecting input weights and analytically determining output weights, thereby overcoming the limitations of traditional gradient-based training methods. Experimental results demonstrate that ELM achieves superior generalization performance and faster learning times compared to conventional neural network training techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G423</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2606974598">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel architecture for abstractive text summarization using hybrid pointer-generator networks, which enhance the accuracy of information reproduction and reduce repetition in generated summaries. By applying this approach to the CNN/Daily Mail dataset, the authors demonstrate a significant improvement over existing state-of-the-art models, achieving at least a 2 ROUGE point increase.</data>
      <data key="d2">G424</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2107034620">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel Bayesian Hierarchical Model for learning and recognizing natural scene categories without the need for expert annotations, utilizing unsupervised learning to represent images through local regions and themes. The method demonstrates effective categorization performance across a diverse set of 13 complex scene categories.</data>
      <data key="d2">G425</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1623080549">
      <data key="d1">The article provides an overview of fundamental principles and techniques in pattern recognition, focusing on various methods for designing and analyzing recognition systems, including decision functions, classification approaches, and feature selection. It also explores applications in image analysis, machine learning, and deep learning within the context of automatic classification and fuzzy pattern recognition.</data>
      <data key="d2">G426</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963626623">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Bag of Tricks for Efficient Text Classification&quot; by Armand Joulin et al. presents various techniques and methodologies aimed at improving the efficiency of text classification tasks in natural language processing, leveraging advancements in machine learning and deep learning to enhance document classification performance.</data>
      <data key="d2">G427</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2125027820">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses Probabilistic Principal Component Analysis (PPCA), a method that enhances traditional PCA by incorporating a probabilistic framework through maximum likelihood estimation in a latent variable model. It highlights the advantages of this approach, including an iterative EM algorithm for estimating subspaces, and provides illustrative examples to demonstrate its effectiveness in data processing and analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G428</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4210257598">
      <data key="d1">This article offers a comprehensive overview of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), categorizing them into four main types and discussing their applications across various fields, while also summarizing open-source resources and potential future research directions in this rapidly evolving area of machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G429</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2165878107">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive review and tutorial on joint time-frequency distributions, focusing on the fundamental concepts and methods used to analyze how the spectral content of signals varies over time. It aims to make these advanced ideas accessible to non-specialists while highlighting recent significant advancements in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G430</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2963858333">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces Graph Attention Networks (GATs), innovative neural network architectures designed for graph-structured data that utilize masked self-attention layers to improve upon traditional convolution-based methods. GATs effectively assign varying weights to neighborhood features without the need for complex matrix operations, achieving state-of-the-art results on multiple benchmarks, including citation and protein-protein interaction datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G431</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2121601095">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive survey of face detection techniques in images, highlighting the challenges posed by variability in size, shape, and lighting conditions. It categorizes and evaluates existing algorithms, discusses data collection and evaluation metrics, and identifies limitations while suggesting promising directions for future research in the field of computer vision and face processing.</data>
      <data key="d2">G432</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2136796925">
      <data key="d1">This article discusses various Markov chain methods, such as the Gibbs sampler and Metropolis algorithm, for sampling from posterior distributions, while addressing theoretical and practical issues related to convergence rates and variance reduction techniques to enhance the efficiency of these methods in statistical applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G433</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W764651262">
      <data key="d1">The article presents FlowNet, a novel approach to optical flow estimation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which have traditionally excelled in recognition tasks but struggled with optical flow. It introduces two CNN architectures, including one that correlates feature vectors across different image locations, and demonstrates their effectiveness using a synthetic dataset, achieving competitive accuracy and frame rates on established benchmarks.</data>
      <data key="d2">G434</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W4300954432">
      <data key="d1">The article explores the impressive performance of large Convolutional Network models on the ImageNet benchmark, introducing a novel visualization technique to understand intermediate feature layers and classifier operations. It also conducts an ablation study to assess the contributions of different model layers, ultimately demonstrating improved architectures that outperform existing state-of-the-art results on the Caltech-101 and Caltech-256 datasets.</data>
      <data key="d2">G435</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2884367402">
      <data key="d1">This article reviews the advancements in object detection through deep learning, contrasting traditional methods with modern frameworks that leverage convolutional neural networks to learn high-level features. It discusses various architectures, modifications, and specific tasks within the field, providing experimental analyses and insights for future research directions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G436</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2108995755">
      <data key="d1">This article introduces kernel-based learning algorithms, focusing on support vector machines, kernel Fisher discriminant analysis, and principal component analysis, while discussing their theoretical foundations and practical applications in supervised and unsupervised learning scenarios, such as optical character recognition and DNA analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">G437</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2172156083">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel method for real-time 3D human pose recognition from single depth images, utilizing an object recognition approach to simplify the pose estimation process into per-pixel classification. The system achieves high accuracy and operates at 200 frames per second on consumer hardware, demonstrating improved generalization over existing techniques.</data>
      <data key="d2">G438</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1787224781">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses a methodology for interpreting the decisions of non-linear classifiers in automated image systems through pixel-wise explanations using Layer-Wise Relevance Propagation. By visualizing the contributions of individual pixels to classification predictions, the approach aims to enhance understanding and validation of machine learning models, particularly in applications involving image data.</data>
      <data key="d2">G439</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2131613989">
      <data key="d1">The article introduces the comprehensive learning particle swarm optimizer (CLPSO), a novel variant of particle swarm optimization that enhances global optimization of multimodal functions by utilizing the historical best information from all particles to update velocities, thereby preserving diversity and preventing premature convergence. Experimental results on various multimodal test functions indicate that CLPSO outperforms eight recent PSO variants.</data>
      <data key="d2">G440</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2533800772">
      <data key="d1">This article reviews the impact of deep learning on medical image analysis, highlighting its ability to automatically identify, classify, and quantify patterns in images through hierarchical feature representations. It discusses the fundamentals of deep learning methods, their applications in image registration, anatomical structure detection, tissue segmentation, and computer-aided diagnosis, while also addressing current research challenges and future directions for improvement.</data>
      <data key="d2">G441</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W3186179742">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of RoseTTA fold, a three-track neural network model that enhances the accuracy of protein structure and interaction predictions, building on the success of DeepMind's Alphafold2. This innovative approach allows for simultaneous processing of sequence, distance, and coordinate information, effectively addressing complex modeling challenges in protein science.</data>
      <data key="d2">G442</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2962879692">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses advancements in the training of Wasserstein Generative Adversarial Networks (WGANs), addressing issues of instability and poor sample generation caused by weight clipping. It introduces a new method that penalizes the gradient norm of the critic with respect to its input, resulting in improved performance across various architectures and high-quality outputs in datasets like CIFAR-10 and LSUN bedrooms.</data>
      <data key="d2">G443</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2125283600">
      <data key="d1">The article provides a comprehensive survey of decision tree classifier methodologies, exploring their design, feature selection, and search strategies, while also addressing existing challenges and comparing decision trees with neural networks in the context of machine learning and classification systems.</data>
      <data key="d2">G444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1978239142">
      <data key="d1">This article provides a comprehensive tutorial on statistical procedures for identifying outlying observations in sample data, focusing on methods to determine whether extreme values are significant outliers. It includes formulae and examples to illustrate the application of these techniques in various fields such as biostatistics and machine learning.</data>
      <data key="d2">G445</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2019502123">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a fast fixed-point algorithm for independent component analysis (ICA), designed for blind source separation and feature extraction, which converges to the most accurate solution without user-defined parameters. It demonstrates that this algorithm is significantly faster than traditional gradient-based methods, achieving convergence in a cubic time complexity while effectively identifying non-Gaussian components across various probability distributions.</data>
      <data key="d2">G446</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2603777577">
      <data key="d1">The article presents a novel approach to real-time arbitrary style transfer using a technique called adaptive instance normalization (AdaIN), which allows for flexible user controls and achieves comparable speed to existing methods without being limited to predefined styles. This advancement addresses the limitations of previous neural algorithms that required slow iterative processes, enabling efficient and dynamic style transfer in images.</data>
      <data key="d2">G447</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2141125852">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the development of multi-column deep neural networks that achieve near-human performance in image classification tasks, such as recognizing handwritten digits and traffic signs, by utilizing biologically inspired architectures and winner-take-all neuron strategies. The proposed method significantly outperforms traditional approaches and sets new benchmarks in various image classification challenges.</data>
      <data key="d2">G448</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2105101328">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses advancements in action recognition through the enhancement of dense trajectories by correcting for camera motion using a combination of SURF descriptors and optical flow. By employing robust homography with RANSAC and integrating human detection to filter out inconsistent matches, the proposed method significantly improves performance on several challenging datasets, surpassing current state-of-the-art results.</data>
      <data key="d2">G449</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W1815076433">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the challenges of training Recurrent Neural Networks, specifically focusing on the vanishing and exploding gradient problems. It presents an analytical and geometric dynamical systems perspective to better understand these issues and proposes a norm clipping strategy as an effective solution, supported by empirical validation.</data>
      <data key="d2">G450</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2025444507">
      <data key="d1">This article presents a novel neural-network representation of density-functional theory (DFT) potential-energy surfaces, enabling significantly faster and accurate calculations of energy and forces for both periodic and nonperiodic systems, thereby facilitating the simulation of large chemical processes that are typically computationally intensive. The method is demonstrated to be highly effective for bulk silicon, outperforming traditional empirical potentials.</data>
      <data key="d2">G451</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2155399784">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses an orthogonal least-squares learning algorithm for radial basis function networks, presenting it as a more effective alternative to traditional methods that rely on random selection of data points as centers. The proposed algorithm systematically selects centers to maximize explained variance, addressing issues of numerical ill-conditioning and enhancing the efficiency of network fitting in signal processing applications.</data>
      <data key="d2">G452</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2076118331">
      <data key="d1">The article discusses the bias/variance dilemma in the context of feedforward neural networks trained through error backpropagation, highlighting their strengths and weaknesses as nonparametric regression estimators. It emphasizes the limitations of current-generation networks in addressing complex machine perception problems and suggests that the challenges lie more in representation modeling than in the learning process itself.</data>
      <data key="d2">G453</data>
    </node>
    <node id="https://openalex.org/W2124868070">
      <data key="d1">The article &quot;Combining Pattern Classifiers: Methods and Algorithms&quot; discusses various techniques and algorithms for integrating multiple pattern classifiers to enhance performance in statistical pattern recognition and machine learning applications. It explores the significance of classifier systems in automatic classification and presents insights into current research in the field.</data>
      <data key="d2">G454</data>
    </node>
    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2963446712" target="https://openalex.org/W2194775991">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Densely Connected Convolutional Networks was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; by proposing a new architecture (DenseNet) that enhances feature propagation and alleviates training difficulties associated with deeper networks. While both papers address the challenges of training deep neural networks, the child paper extends the parent paper's findings by introducing a novel connection strategy that improves performance on various object recognition tasks.</data>
      <data key="d5">4</data>
      <data key="d6">G455</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2618530766" target="https://openalex.org/W2194775991">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article ImageNet classification with deep convolutional neural networks was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by utilizing deep convolutional neural networks for image classification, achieving improved performance metrics on the ImageNet dataset. While the parent paper introduces a residual learning framework for training deeper networks, the child paper applies these principles to enhance classification accuracy, demonstrating the effectiveness of its approach in comparison to previous state-of-the-art results.</data>
      <data key="d5">9</data>
      <data key="d6">G456</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W639708223" target="https://openalex.org/W2194775991">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Faster R-CNN: Towards Real-Time Object Detection with Region Proposal Networks was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Faster R-CNN: Towards Real-Time Object Detection with Region Proposal Networks,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; by leveraging the deep residual learning framework to enhance object detection through the introduction of Region Proposal Networks. It extends the parent paper's findings by applying the principles of deep learning to improve the efficiency and accuracy of object detection tasks.</data>
      <data key="d5">7</data>
      <data key="d6">G457</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2963150697" target="https://openalex.org/W2194775991">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Mask R-CNN was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Mask R-CNN,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; by utilizing the residual learning framework to enhance object instance segmentation. It extends the capabilities of Faster R-CNN, which is likely influenced by the deep learning techniques discussed in the parent paper, thereby inheriting and applying its principles to achieve improved performance in segmentation tasks.</data>
      <data key="d5">7</data>
      <data key="d6">G458</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2565639579" target="https://openalex.org/W2194775991">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Feature Pyramid Networks for Object Detection was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Feature Pyramid Networks for Object Detection,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; by leveraging the deep residual learning framework to enhance multi-scale object detection through the development of a novel architecture. While the parent paper establishes the importance of deep representations for visual recognition tasks, the child paper extends this work by specifically applying these principles to improve performance in object detection tasks, demonstrating significant advancements in accuracy and efficiency.</data>
      <data key="d5">6</data>
      <data key="d6">G459</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2962793481" target="https://openalex.org/W2194775991">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Unpaired Image-to-Image Translation Using Cycle-Consistent Adversarial Networks was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper on unpaired image-to-image translation using cycle-consistent adversarial networks builds on the foundational concepts of deep learning and image representation introduced in the parent paper on deep residual learning for image recognition. While the child paper does not directly reference the parent paper's specific methodologies, it extends the application of deep learning techniques to a new domain of unpaired image translation, demonstrating the versatility of deep neural networks in addressing different challenges in computer vision.</data>
