      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;ECA-Net: Efficient Channel Attention for Deep Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; by proposing an efficient channel attention mechanism that enhances the performance of deep convolutional neural networks, specifically leveraging the residual learning framework. While the child paper extends the parent’s work by introducing a novel module that reduces complexity while improving accuracy, it also empirically evaluates its performance against established architectures like ResNet, which are derived from the parent paper.</data>
