      <data key="d3">In 2019, article Object Detection With Deep Learning: A Review was published and referenced article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Object Detection With Deep Learning: A Review,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; by discussing the advancements in deep learning architectures, including residual networks, and their application to various object detection tasks. It extends the parent paper's findings by reviewing and comparing different learning-based frameworks and their performance in object detection, thereby situating the residual learning approach within a broader context of deep learning developments.</data>
