      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; builds on the foundational work presented in the parent paper, &quot;ImageNet Classification with Deep Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; by introducing a residual learning framework that enables the training of significantly deeper neural networks, thereby extending the capabilities and performance benchmarks established in the parent paper. The child paper not only references the parent but also demonstrates improved accuracy and efficiency in image recognition tasks through deeper architectures.</data>
