      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;ImageNet Classification with Deep Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; by proposing a novel architecture (DenseNet) that enhances feature propagation and reduces the number of parameters through dense connections between layers. While the parent paper establishes a foundational deep learning model for image classification, the child paper extends this work by addressing limitations such as the vanishing gradient problem and demonstrating significant performance improvements on competitive benchmarks.</data>
