      <data key="d3">In 2015, article Going deeper with convolutions was published and referenced article Gradient-based learning applied to document recognition that was published in 1998</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Going deeper with convolutions,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of neural networks and gradient-based learning introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Gradient-based learning applied to document recognition,&quot; by proposing a novel deep convolutional neural network architecture (GoogLeNet) that enhances classification and detection performance. While the parent paper discusses the effectiveness of convolutional networks for character recognition, the child paper extends this work by optimizing network depth and width for improved resource utilization and performance in image classification tasks.</data>
