      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of convolutional networks discussed in the parent paper, &quot;Gradient-based learning applied to document recognition,&quot; by introducing a novel architecture (DenseNet) that enhances feature propagation and addresses issues like the vanishing gradient problem. While the parent paper focuses on the application of gradient-based learning in document recognition, the child paper extends this work by proposing a new network structure that achieves superior performance on various object recognition tasks.</data>
