      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Going Deeper with Convolutions,&quot; by proposing a novel architecture (DenseNet) that enhances feature propagation and addresses issues like the vanishing gradient problem, while also achieving improved performance on benchmark tasks compared to existing models, including those discussed in the parent paper.</data>
