      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;MobileNetV2: Inverted Residuals and Linear Bottlenecks,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Going deeper with convolutions,&quot; by enhancing the architecture for mobile applications and improving performance on various tasks while maintaining efficiency. It extends the ideas of deep convolutional networks and resource optimization by introducing novel structures like inverted residuals and linear bottlenecks, thereby inheriting and advancing the principles established in the parent work.</data>
