      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;SegNet,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Going Deeper with Convolutions,&quot; by utilizing a deep convolutional architecture for image segmentation, while also comparing its performance against other established models like FCN and DeepLab. SegNet specifically inherits design principles from the parent paper's Inception architecture, adapting them for efficient pixel-wise segmentation tasks.</data>
