      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Spatial Pyramid Pooling in Deep Convolutional Networks for Visual Recognition,&quot; builds on the parent paper, &quot;Going Deeper with Convolutions,&quot; by introducing a new pooling strategy that enhances the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in visual recognition tasks, particularly by allowing for variable input sizes and improving classification accuracy. While the child paper references the parent paper's architecture, it extends the existing work by proposing a novel method that achieves state-of-the-art results on benchmark datasets.</data>
