      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;A survey on Image Data Augmentation for Deep Learning,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; by discussing data augmentation techniques that can enhance the performance of deep learning models, including those based on architectures like DenseNet. While the child paper does not directly compare experimental results with the parent paper, it extends the discussion by exploring methods to improve model training in scenarios where data is limited, thereby inheriting the principles of deep learning from the parent work.</data>
