      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Learning Transferable Architectures for Scalable Image Recognition,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; by proposing a novel architecture search method that enhances model transferability and generalization in image recognition tasks. It extends the foundational ideas of DenseNet by introducing new architectural components and techniques, such as the NASNet space and ScheduledDropPath, to achieve state-of-the-art performance on benchmark datasets.</data>
