      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;ECA-Net: Efficient Channel Attention for Deep Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; by proposing an Efficient Channel Attention module that enhances the performance of deep convolutional networks while maintaining low model complexity. It extends the ideas of feature propagation and efficiency in CNNs, as discussed in the parent paper, by introducing a novel approach to channel attention that avoids dimensionality reduction.</data>
