      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;YOLOv7: Trainable Bag-of-Freebies Sets New State-of-the-Art for Real-Time Object Detectors,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of convolutional networks introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; by leveraging advanced architectural optimizations and training techniques to achieve superior performance in real-time object detection. While the child paper does not directly compare its results with the parent paper, it extends the principles of DenseNet to enhance detection capabilities, indicating a scholarly progression from the parent to the child work.</data>
