    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2963446712" target="https://openalex.org/W2095705004">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Densely Connected Convolutional Networks was published and referenced article Dropout: a simple way to prevent neural networks from overfitting that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Dropout: a simple way to prevent neural networks from overfitting,&quot; by proposing a novel architecture (DenseNet) that enhances feature propagation and addresses issues like the vanishing gradient problem, which are relevant to training deep neural networks. While the parent paper focuses on regularization techniques to prevent overfitting, the child paper extends this work by introducing a new network structure that improves performance on various object recognition tasks.</data>
      <data key="d5">4</data>
