    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W1836465849" target="https://openalex.org/W2095705004">
      <data key="d3">In 2015, article Batch Normalization: Accelerating Deep Network Training by Reducing Internal Covariate Shift was published and referenced article Dropout: a simple way to prevent neural networks from overfitting that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper on Batch Normalization builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper on Dropout by addressing the issue of internal covariate shift during training in deep neural networks, thereby extending the discussion of regularization techniques. While both papers focus on improving the training and performance of neural networks, the child paper specifically enhances the training process by incorporating normalization as a structural component, rather than merely comparing performance with the dropout method.</data>
      <data key="d5">4</data>
