      <data key="d3">In 2015, article Batch Normalization: Accelerating Deep Network Training by Reducing Internal Covariate Shift was published and referenced article Dropout: a simple way to prevent neural networks from overfitting that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper on Batch Normalization builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper on Dropout by addressing the issue of internal covariate shift during training in deep neural networks, which complements the regularization approach of Dropout. While both papers tackle challenges in training deep networks, the child paper extends the discussion by proposing a novel normalization technique that enhances training efficiency and model performance.</data>
