      <data key="d3">In 2015, article Distilling the Knowledge in a Neural Network was published and referenced article Dropout: a simple way to prevent neural networks from overfitting that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Distilling the Knowledge in a Neural Network,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Dropout: a simple way to prevent neural networks from overfitting,&quot; by further developing the idea of model compression and knowledge distillation to improve the deployment of neural networks. While the parent paper addresses overfitting through dropout, the child paper extends this by proposing a method to distill knowledge from multiple models into a single, more efficient model, thereby enhancing performance and usability in practical applications.</data>
