      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Dual Attention Network for Scene Segmentation,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Fully Convolutional Networks for Semantic Segmentation,&quot; by introducing a novel Dual Attention Network (DANet) that enhances feature representation through the integration of local and global contextual dependencies. While the parent paper establishes the efficacy of fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation, the child paper extends this work by proposing a new architecture that achieves state-of-the-art performance on multiple datasets.</data>
