      <data key="d3">In 2016, article Deep Convolutional Neural Networks for Computer-Aided Detection: CNN Architectures, Dataset Characteristics and Transfer Learning was published and referenced article Fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation that was published in 2015</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by utilizing the foundational concepts of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and transfer learning introduced in the parent paper to address specific challenges in computer-aided detection (CAD) for medical imaging. It extends the application of fully convolutional networks to new tasks, such as thoraco-abdominal lymph node classification and interstitial lung disease detection, while also exploring architectural variations and dataset characteristics.</data>
