      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Deformable Convolutional Networks was published and referenced article Fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation that was published in 2015</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deformable Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Fully Convolutional Networks for Semantic Segmentation,&quot; by enhancing the geometric transformation capabilities of convolutional neural networks through the introduction of deformable convolution and RoI pooling modules. It extends the parent paper's work by proposing new methods that improve performance on complex vision tasks, demonstrating the effectiveness of dense deep learning architectures in semantic segmentation and object detection.</data>
