      <data key="d3">In 2016, article Context Encoders: Feature Learning by Inpainting was published and referenced article Fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation that was published in 2015</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Context Encoders: Feature Learning by Inpainting,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of convolutional networks presented in the parent paper, &quot;Fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation,&quot; by introducing a novel unsupervised feature learning algorithm that leverages context-based pixel prediction. While the parent paper focuses on semantic segmentation using fully convolutional networks, the child paper extends this work by applying similar principles to the task of inpainting, demonstrating the effectiveness of learned features in various computer vision tasks.</data>
