      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of convolutional networks introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Fully Convolutional Networks for Semantic Segmentation,&quot; by proposing a residual learning framework that enables the training of significantly deeper networks for improved image recognition tasks. While the parent paper focuses on semantic segmentation, the child paper extends this work by demonstrating how deeper architectures can enhance performance in image classification and object detection, thereby inheriting and advancing the methodologies established in the parent paper.</data>
