      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;FCOS: Fully Convolutional One-Stage Object Detection,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation,&quot; by applying the fully convolutional architecture to the task of object detection without relying on anchor boxes. It extends the parent paper's framework to propose a novel, simpler approach for instance-level tasks, demonstrating improved accuracy in object detection.</data>
