      <data key="d3">In 2016, article You Only Look Once: Unified, Real-Time Object Detection was published and referenced article Faster R-CNN: Towards Real-Time Object Detection with Region Proposal Networks that was published in 2017</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;You Only Look Once: Unified, Real-Time Object Detection,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Faster R-CNN: Towards Real-Time Object Detection with Region Proposal Networks,&quot; by proposing a novel approach to object detection that frames the task as a regression problem rather than relying on region proposal networks. While the child paper acknowledges the limitations of existing methods, including Faster R-CNN, it extends the field by introducing a unified architecture that optimizes performance for real-time applications.</data>
