      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deformable Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the parent paper, &quot;Rich Feature Hierarchies for Accurate Object Detection and Semantic Segmentation,&quot; by introducing new modules that enhance the transformation modeling capabilities of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), thereby extending the foundational concepts of CNNs applied in the parent work. It validates its approach through extensive experiments, indicating a progression in the field of object detection and semantic segmentation.</data>
