      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;You Only Look Once: Unified, Real-Time Object Detection,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Fast R-CNN,&quot; by proposing a novel approach to object detection that frames the task as a regression problem and optimizes the entire pipeline for real-time performance. While it acknowledges the limitations of existing methods, including Fast R-CNN, it extends the field by introducing a unified architecture that achieves faster processing speeds and improved generalization across various domains.</data>
