      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by applying the gradient boosting framework introduced in &quot;Greedy function approximation: A gradient boosting machine&quot; to develop a practical guide for using boosted regression trees (BRT) in ecological modeling. It extends the theoretical concepts of boosting and tree-based methods by demonstrating their application and advantages in handling ecological data, thus providing a tutorial for ecologists.</data>
