      <data key="d3">In 2017, article LightGBM: A Highly Efficient Gradient Boosting Decision Tree was published and referenced article Greedy function approximation: A gradient boosting machine. that was published in 2001</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;LightGBM: A Highly Efficient Gradient Boosting Decision Tree,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Greedy function approximation: A gradient boosting machine,&quot; by introducing novel techniques to enhance the efficiency and scalability of gradient boosting decision trees. Specifically, it extends the parent paper's framework by implementing Gradient-based One-Side Sampling (GOSS) and Exclusive Feature Bundling (EFB) to improve performance in high-dimensional datasets.</data>
