      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by applying the principles of machine learning, specifically random forests, to ecological classification tasks, while also comparing the performance of random forests against traditional classifiers. It extends the concepts introduced in the parent paper by demonstrating their applicability in a specific ecological context and validating their effectiveness through empirical results.</data>
