      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Aggregated Residual Transformations for Deep Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Mask R-CNN,&quot; by proposing a new network architecture (ResNeXt) that enhances image classification performance through aggregated transformations. While the parent paper focuses on object instance segmentation, the child paper extends the discussion to classification tasks, demonstrating improved accuracy and efficiency compared to existing models, including those based on the parent paper's framework.</data>
