      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Non-local Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Mask R-CNN,&quot; by proposing a new non-local operation that enhances the ability to capture long-range dependencies in various vision architectures, including those used for tasks like video classification and object detection. While the child paper does not directly compare performance with the parent paper, it extends the foundational ideas of neural network architectures to improve upon existing methods in the field.</data>
