      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;YOLOv4: Optimal Speed and Accuracy of Object Detection,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of object detection established by the parent paper, &quot;Mask R-CNN,&quot; by introducing new features and techniques to enhance speed and accuracy in real-time object detection. While it does not directly compare performance with Mask R-CNN, it extends the field by proposing improvements that aim to achieve state-of-the-art results on the MS COCO dataset.</data>
