      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Least Squares Generative Adversarial Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Image-to-Image Translation with Conditional Adversarial Networks,&quot; by proposing a modification to the GAN framework that addresses the vanishing gradients problem and enhances image generation quality and stability. While the parent paper focuses on conditional adversarial networks for image-to-image translation, the child paper extends this work by introducing least squares as a loss function for improved performance in generative tasks.</data>
