      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Hierarchical Attention Networks for Document Classification,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of neural networks introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Convolutional Neural Networks for Sentence Classification,&quot; by extending the application of deep learning techniques from sentence-level to document-level classification tasks. While both papers focus on classification using neural networks, the child paper specifically enhances the methodology by introducing hierarchical attention mechanisms, thereby inheriting and advancing the parent paper's work in the field of natural language processing.</data>
