      <data key="d3">In 2016, article Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition was published and referenced article Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks that was published in 2010</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks,&quot; by introducing a residual learning framework that addresses the challenges of training deeper networks and demonstrating its effectiveness through empirical results. Specifically, the child paper extends the parent paper's insights on training deep architectures by providing a novel approach that allows for significantly deeper networks while improving performance on image recognition tasks.</data>
