      <data key="d3">In 2015, article Delving Deep into Rectifiers: Surpassing Human-Level Performance on ImageNet Classification was published and referenced article Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks that was published in 2010</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by proposing a new activation function, the Parametric Linear Unit (PReLU), and a robust initialization method that enhance the training of deep neural networks, specifically in the context of image classification. It extends the findings of the parent paper regarding the challenges of training deep networks by providing practical solutions that lead to improved performance on the ImageNet dataset.</data>
