      <data key="d3">In 2013, article Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives was published and referenced article Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks that was published in 2010</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks,&quot; by exploring advanced techniques in representation learning and their implications for machine learning. It extends the discussion of neural network training by reviewing recent developments in unsupervised feature learning and raising new questions about representation objectives, thereby inheriting and expanding upon the insights from the parent paper.</data>
