      <data key="d3">In 2012, article Deep Neural Networks for Acoustic Modeling in Speech Recognition: The Shared Views of Four Research Groups was published and referenced article Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks that was published in 2010</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by applying the insights gained from the training of deep feedforward neural networks to the specific context of acoustic modeling in speech recognition, highlighting the advancements in deep neural networks (DNNs) that outperform traditional models. It references the foundational concepts of DNN training and performance improvements discussed in the parent paper while focusing on their application in speech recognition systems.</data>
