      <data key="d3">In 2011, article Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks was published and referenced article Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks that was published in 2010</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks,&quot; by exploring the implications of using rectifying activation functions in deep neural networks, which addresses the challenges of training highlighted in the parent paper. It extends the discussion on activation functions and their impact on network performance, suggesting that rectifying non-linearities can yield comparable results despite their inherent difficulties.</data>
