      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks,&quot; by introducing a residual learning framework that addresses the challenges of training deeper networks. It extends the parent paper's insights into the training dynamics of deep architectures by demonstrating the effectiveness of significantly deeper networks in achieving improved performance on image recognition tasks.</data>
