      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Unpaired Image-to-Image Translation Using Cycle-Consistent Adversarial Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Photo-Realistic Single Image Super-Resolution Using a Generative Adversarial Network,&quot; by applying adversarial training techniques to a different problem domain—unpaired image-to-image translation—while leveraging the foundational principles of generative adversarial networks (GANs) established in the parent work. The child paper extends the parent paper's methodology by introducing cycle consistency loss to address the challenges of unpaired data, thereby enhancing the applicability of GANs in various image translation tasks.</data>
