      <data key="d3">In 2013, article 3D Convolutional Neural Networks for Human Action Recognition was published and referenced article Experiments with a new boosting algorithm that was published in 1996</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper on 3D Convolutional Neural Networks for Human Action Recognition builds on the foundational concepts of deep learning and classification introduced in the parent paper about the boosting algorithm, specifically by applying advanced neural network techniques to enhance action recognition in video data. While the parent paper focuses on boosting algorithms for improving classifier performance, the child paper extends this by implementing a novel 3D CNN approach that captures both spatial and temporal features for superior action recognition results.</data>
