    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2982770724" target="https://openalex.org/W2964350391">
      <data key="d3">In 2019, article FCOS: Fully Convolutional One-Stage Object Detection was published and referenced article Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning that was published in 2017</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;FCOS: Fully Convolutional One-Stage Object Detection,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of deep convolutional networks introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning,&quot; by applying advanced techniques in object detection that leverage the benefits of convolutional architectures without relying on anchor boxes. While the child paper does not directly compare performance with the parent paper, it extends the discussion of convolutional network applications by proposing a novel, simpler framework for object detection that improves accuracy.</data>
