      <data key="d3">In 2019, article ALBERT: A Lite BERT for Self-supervised Learning of Language Representations was published and referenced article Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning that was published in 2017</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;ALBERT: A Lite BERT for Self-supervised Learning of Language Representations,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of model efficiency and performance improvements in natural language processing, similar to the advancements discussed in the parent paper, &quot;Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning.&quot; While the parent paper focuses on convolutional networks and residual connections, the child paper extends the discussion to language models by introducing parameter-reduction techniques and self-supervised learning methods that enhance performance on various benchmarks.</data>
