    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2963091558" target="https://openalex.org/W1522734439">
      <data key="d3">In 2018, article Non-local Neural Networks was published and referenced article Learning Spatiotemporal Features with 3D Convolutional Networks that was published in 2015</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Non-local Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the parent paper, &quot;Learning Spatiotemporal Features with 3D Convolutional Networks,&quot; by introducing a novel non-local operation that captures long-range dependencies, which can enhance the performance of various vision architectures, including those utilizing 3D ConvNets. While the parent paper focuses on spatiotemporal feature learning through 3D convolutions, the child paper extends this work by proposing a method that improves performance on video classification and other tasks by addressing the limitations of local operations.</data>
