    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2963524571" target="https://openalex.org/W1522734439">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Quo Vadis, Action Recognition? A New Model and the Kinetics Dataset was published and referenced article Learning Spatiotemporal Features with 3D Convolutional Networks that was published in 2015</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by introducing a new model (the Two-Stream Inflated 3D ConvNet) that extends the concepts of spatiotemporal feature learning from 3D ConvNets, while also leveraging a significantly larger dataset (Kinetics) to improve action recognition performance. It evaluates and demonstrates the effectiveness of this new model against the benchmarks established in the parent paper, thereby inheriting and enhancing its foundational ideas.</data>
