      <data key="d3">In 2016, article Real-Time Single Image and Video Super-Resolution Using an Efficient Sub-Pixel Convolutional Neural Network was published and referenced article Learning Spatiotemporal Features with 3D Convolutional Networks that was published in 2015</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by utilizing concepts from deep convolutional networks to propose a novel architecture for real-time single image and video super-resolution. It extends the parent paper's findings by introducing an efficient sub-pixel convolution layer that enhances performance and reduces complexity in the super-resolution process.</data>
