      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;YOLOv4: Optimal Speed and Accuracy of Object Detection,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) discussed in the parent paper, &quot;EfficientNet: Rethinking Model Scaling for Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; by introducing new features and techniques to enhance object detection performance. While the parent paper focuses on model scaling for improved efficiency, the child paper applies these principles to achieve state-of-the-art results in real-time object detection, thereby extending the application of CNN advancements.</data>
