      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Photo-Realistic Single Image Super-Resolution Using a Generative Adversarial Network was published and referenced article Image Super-Resolution Using Deep Convolutional Networks that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Photo-Realistic Single Image Super-Resolution Using a Generative Adversarial Network,&quot; builds on the foundational work presented in the parent paper, &quot;Image Super-Resolution Using Deep Convolutional Networks,&quot; by introducing a novel generative adversarial network (SRGAN) that enhances the quality of super-resolved images through a perceptual loss function, thereby addressing the limitations of traditional methods in recovering finer texture details. While the parent paper establishes a deep learning approach for single image super-resolution, the child paper extends this by focusing on achieving photo-realistic results at higher upscaling factors.</data>
