      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by proposing a more advanced single-image super-resolution method that utilizes a deeper convolutional network architecture and introduces a novel training procedure to enhance accuracy and convergence speed. While both papers focus on deep learning approaches for super-resolution, the child paper extends the techniques presented in the parent paper to achieve improved performance metrics.</data>
