      <data key="d4">The child paper on image data augmentation builds on the foundational concepts of deep learning and feature extraction presented in the parent paper, FaceNet, by exploring techniques to enhance dataset quality and size, which are crucial for improving model performance in tasks like face recognition. While the child paper does not directly reference FaceNet's specific methodologies, it extends the discussion of deep learning applications by addressing the challenges of overfitting in scenarios with limited data, thereby inheriting the broader context of deep learning advancements.</data>
