      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;DeepFool: A Simple and Accurate Method to Fool Deep Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the findings of the parent paper, &quot;Intriguing properties of neural networks,&quot; by proposing the DeepFool algorithm to effectively compute adversarial perturbations that exploit the discontinuous input-output mappings identified in the parent work. This relationship indicates that the child paper extends the understanding of neural network vulnerabilities discussed in the parent paper.</data>
