      <data key="d3">In 2016, article Neural Machine Translation of Rare Words with Subword Units was published and referenced article Learning Phrase Representations using RNN Encoder-Decoder for Statistical Machine Translation that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by extending the concepts of neural machine translation (NMT) by introducing a method for handling rare words through subword units, which enhances the fixed vocabulary approach discussed in the parent paper's RNN Encoder-Decoder model. While the parent paper focuses on phrase representations in statistical machine translation, the child paper empirically demonstrates improvements in translation performance by addressing the out-of-vocabulary problem, thus inheriting and advancing the foundational ideas presented in the parent work.</data>
