      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by analyzing the properties of the RNN Encoder-Decoder model introduced in the parent paper, specifically focusing on its performance with varying sentence lengths and its ability to learn grammatical structures. While the child paper extends the discussion of neural machine translation, it does not merely compare performance but rather investigates the implications of the model's architecture in greater detail.</data>
