      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Convolutional LSTM Network: A Machine Learning Approach for Precipitation Nowcasting,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Learning Phrase Representations using RNN Encoder-Decoder for Statistical Machine Translation,&quot; by extending the architecture to incorporate convolutional structures for spatiotemporal sequence prediction in weather forecasting. While both papers utilize RNNs, the child paper specifically adapts and enhances the RNN framework to address a different application domain, demonstrating the versatility of the underlying neural network principles.</data>
