      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by extending the RNN Encoder-Decoder model to incorporate a soft alignment mechanism, enhancing the performance of neural machine translation beyond the traditional statistical methods discussed in the parent paper. It proposes a novel approach that allows the model to automatically identify relevant parts of the input for generating target words, thereby improving translation quality.</data>
