      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper by applying support vector machines (SVMs) as classifiers in its feature selection methodology, specifically utilizing mutual information criteria to enhance feature selection for pattern classification systems. While the parent paper focuses on comparing different multiclass SVM methods, the child paper extends this by integrating SVMs into a new feature selection framework, demonstrating improved accuracy through experimental validation.</data>
