      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by proposing a unified learning framework that simplifies and extends the application of least square support vector machines (LS-SVM) and proximal support vector machines (PSVM) for regression and multiclass classification, while also comparing its performance against traditional SVM methods discussed in the parent paper. It highlights the advantages of the Extreme Learning Machine (ELM) approach in terms of scalability and generalization performance, thus inheriting and expanding upon the concepts introduced in the parent paper.</data>
