      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by extending the concept of denoising autoencoders to create stacked architectures that improve performance on classification tasks, demonstrating lower error rates and enhanced feature learning. It also introduces qualitative experiments that highlight the advantages of the proposed method over traditional autoencoders, thereby inheriting and advancing the foundational ideas presented in the parent paper.</data>
