      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;A Comprehensive Survey on Graph Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of deep learning and feature extraction introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Extracting and composing robust features with denoising autoencoders,&quot; by extending the discussion to the specific domain of graph neural networks (GNNs) and proposing a new taxonomy for categorizing them. While the parent paper focuses on denoising autoencoders and their application in feature learning, the child paper synthesizes and expands upon these ideas within the context of non-Euclidean data structures, thereby inheriting and extending the principles of representation learning.</data>
