      <data key="d3">In 2017, article MobileNets: Efficient Convolutional Neural Networks for Mobile Vision Applications was published and referenced article SqueezeNet: AlexNet-level accuracy with 50x fewer parameters and &lt;0.5MB model size that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;MobileNets,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;SqueezeNet,&quot; by proposing a new class of efficient models that utilize depth-wise separable convolutions to achieve lightweight deep neural networks for mobile applications. While both papers focus on optimizing neural network architectures for performance and efficiency, the child paper extends the parent paper's ideas by introducing global hyper-parameters for balancing latency and accuracy in mobile vision tasks.</data>
