      <data key="d3">In 2018, article ShuffleNet: An Extremely Efficient Convolutional Neural Network for Mobile Devices was published and referenced article SqueezeNet: AlexNet-level accuracy with 50x fewer parameters and &lt;0.5MB model size that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;ShuffleNet,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;SqueezeNet,&quot; by proposing a new convolutional neural network architecture that emphasizes computational efficiency for mobile devices while achieving competitive accuracy. It extends the discussion of lightweight neural network architectures by introducing novel operations to further reduce computation costs compared to existing models like MobileNet, which is referenced in the context of performance comparison.</data>
