      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by utilizing deep learning features, specifically those from architectures like SqueezeNet, to evaluate perceptual similarity in images, demonstrating that these features outperform traditional metrics. While the parent paper focuses on model efficiency and accuracy, the child paper extends this work by exploring the effectiveness of deep features in perceptual tasks, thereby contributing to the understanding of visual representation in machine learning.</data>
