      <data key="d4">The child paper &quot;Rethinking the Inception Architecture for Computer Vision&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) established in the parent paper &quot;Large-Scale Video Classification with Convolutional Neural Networks&quot; by exploring enhancements to the Inception architecture and benchmarking its performance on image classification tasks. While both papers focus on CNNs, the child paper extends the parent’s work by proposing new methods for efficiency and performance improvements in computer vision applications.</data>
