      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;TensorFlow: a system for large-scale machine learning,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of machine learning and neural networks discussed in the parent paper, &quot;Large-Scale Video Classification with Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; by providing a scalable framework that supports various machine learning applications, including those utilizing CNNs for video classification. While the child paper does not directly compare performance with the parent paper, it extends the discussion by offering a versatile system that enables experimentation with novel training algorithms and optimizations relevant to large-scale machine learning tasks.</data>
