      <data key="d3">In 2015, article Learning Spatiotemporal Features with 3D Convolutional Networks was published and referenced article 3D Convolutional Neural Networks for Human Action Recognition that was published in 2013</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by extending the application of 3D convolutional networks (3D ConvNets) for spatiotemporal feature learning, demonstrating their effectiveness in video datasets and comparing their performance against 2D ConvNets and other state-of-the-art methods. It inherits the foundational concepts of 3D CNNs introduced in the parent paper while providing new insights and empirical results in the context of feature learning and classification.</data>
