      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Quo Vadis, Action Recognition? A New Model and the Kinetics Dataset was published and referenced article 3D Convolutional Neural Networks for Human Action Recognition that was published in 2013</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by introducing a new model, the Two-Stream Inflated 3D ConvNet (I3D), which extends the concepts of 3D convolutional neural networks for action recognition by leveraging a larger dataset (Kinetics) to improve classification performance. It also evaluates the effectiveness of the I3D model against existing benchmarks, demonstrating significant improvements over the methods discussed in the parent paper.</data>
