      <data key="d3">In 2013, article Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives was published and referenced article Natural Language Processing (almost) from Scratch that was published in 2011</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Natural Language Processing (almost) from Scratch,&quot; by exploring the significance of data representation in machine learning and discussing advances in representation learning techniques, including those applicable to natural language processing tasks. While the child paper reviews and synthesizes existing work, it extends the parent paper's ideas by addressing broader questions and methodologies in representation learning beyond the specific applications presented in the parent paper.</data>
