      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Neural Architectures for Named Entity Recognition,&quot; builds on the parent paper, &quot;Natural Language Processing (almost) from Scratch,&quot; by applying the unified neural network architecture proposed in the parent to the specific task of named entity recognition, thereby extending its applicability and exploring its performance in this domain.</data>
