      <data key="d3">In 2020, article Momentum Contrast for Unsupervised Visual Representation Learning was published and referenced article A Simple Framework for Contrastive Learning of Visual Representations that was published in 2020</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Momentum Contrast for Unsupervised Visual Representation Learning,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;A Simple Framework for Contrastive Learning of Visual Representations,&quot; by proposing an enhanced method (MoCo) for contrastive learning that incorporates dynamic queues and moving-averaged encoders. It extends the parent paper's findings by demonstrating that its approach can achieve superior performance in various downstream tasks compared to traditional supervised pre-training methods.</data>
