      <data key="d3">In 2005, article Gaussian Processes for Machine Learning was published and referenced article Theory of reproducing kernels that was published in 1950</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Gaussian Processes for Machine Learning,&quot; builds on the theoretical foundations established in the parent paper, &quot;Theory of Reproducing Kernels,&quot; by applying the concepts of reproducing kernels to develop a comprehensive framework for Gaussian processes in machine learning. It extends the parent paper's content by providing practical algorithms and applications in supervised learning, thereby integrating theoretical insights with practical implementation.</data>
