      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Peeking Inside the Black-Box: A Survey on Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI),&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of machine learning and statistical modeling discussed in the parent paper, &quot;A working guide to boosted regression trees,&quot; by exploring the need for transparency and explainability in AI systems, including those that utilize techniques like boosted regression trees. While the parent paper focuses on the practical application of boosted regression trees in ecological modeling, the child paper extends this discussion to the broader implications of explainable AI in various domains.</data>
