      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Densely Connected Convolutional Networks was published and referenced article Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks that was published in 2011</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Densely Connected Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks,&quot; by proposing a novel architecture (DenseNet) that enhances the training and performance of deep neural networks through the use of dense connections between layers. While the parent paper focuses on the advantages of rectifying non-linearities in neural networks, the child paper extends this work by demonstrating significant improvements in object recognition tasks through its unique network design.</data>
