      <data key="d3">In 2017, article GAN（Generative Adversarial Nets） was published and referenced article Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks that was published in 2011</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper on Generative Adversarial Nets (GANs) builds on the foundational concepts of neural networks discussed in the parent paper about Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks, specifically leveraging the principles of adversarial training and neural network architectures. While the parent paper focuses on the performance of different neuron types in deep learning, the child paper extends this by introducing a novel framework for generative modeling that utilizes a two-player game approach.</data>
