      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the foundational concepts of deep learning and neural networks presented in the parent paper, specifically by applying recurrent neural network architectures to the task of statistical machine translation. While the parent paper focuses on the performance of deep sparse rectifier neural networks, the child paper extends this work by exploring the use of RNN encoder-decoder models for learning phrase representations in natural language processing.</data>
