      <data key="d3">In 2013, article Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives was published and referenced article Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks that was published in 2011</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks,&quot; by exploring advanced techniques in representation learning, including deep learning models that may utilize the insights from the parent paper's findings on neural network performance. While the child paper does not directly compare experimental results with the parent paper, it extends the discussion by reviewing recent advancements in unsupervised feature learning that relate to the principles established in the parent work.</data>
