      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the concepts of neural networks introduced in the parent paper by proposing a novel RNN Encoder-Decoder model for statistical machine translation, which utilizes principles of deep learning to enhance performance in natural language processing tasks. While the parent paper focuses on the advantages of rectifier neurons in deep networks, the child paper extends this foundation by applying recurrent neural network architectures to learn meaningful phrase representations.</data>
