      <data key="d3">In 2008, article LIBLINEAR: A Library for Large Linear Classification was published and referenced article A Practical Guide to Support Vector Classication that was published in 2008</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;LIBLINEAR: A Library for Large Linear Classification,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;A Practical Guide to Support Vector Classification,&quot; by providing a practical implementation of support vector machines and logistic regression for large-scale classification tasks. While the parent paper offers guidance on using SVM effectively, the child paper extends this by presenting a library that facilitates the application of these techniques in real-world scenarios.</data>
