      <data key="d3">In 2010, article The Extended Cohn-Kanade Dataset (CK+): A complete dataset for action unit and emotion-specified expression was published and referenced article A Practical Guide to Support Vector Classication that was published in 2008</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;The Extended Cohn-Kanade Dataset (CK+),&quot; builds on the parent paper, &quot;A Practical Guide to Support Vector Classification,&quot; by applying the support vector machine (SVM) classification technique discussed in the parent paper to the context of facial expression recognition using the newly introduced CK+ dataset. It extends the application of SVM by providing baseline results and addressing limitations in emotion labeling and performance evaluation in facial expression research.</data>
