      <data key="d3">In 2010, article Understanding the difficulty of training deep feedforward neural networks was published and referenced article Learning Deep Architectures for AI that was published in 2009</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by analyzing the challenges and mechanisms involved in training deep feedforward neural networks, specifically addressing issues related to activation functions and gradient behavior, which are foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper regarding deep architectures for AI. Additionally, it proposes a new training scheme aimed at improving convergence, extending the insights provided in the parent paper.</data>
