      <data key="d3">In 2013, article Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives was published and referenced article Learning Deep Architectures for AI that was published in 2009</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Representation Learning: A Review and New Perspectives,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Learning Deep Architectures for AI,&quot; by reviewing recent advancements in unsupervised feature learning and representation learning, which are essential for developing deep architectures. It extends the discussion by exploring unanswered questions and new perspectives in the field, thereby inheriting and elaborating on the principles outlined in the parent paper.</data>
