      <data key="d3">In 2014, article Intriguing properties of neural networks was published and referenced article Learning Deep Architectures for AI that was published in 2009</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by exploring the implications of deep neural networks' expressiveness and their potential for learning uninterpretable solutions, which extends the discussion on deep architectures and their capabilities in representing high-level abstractions. Additionally, it investigates specific phenomena related to network behavior, such as misclassification due to imperceptible perturbations, thereby providing empirical insights that complement the theoretical foundations laid in the parent paper.</data>
