      <data key="d3">In 2008, article Extracting and composing robust features with denoising autoencoders was published and referenced article Learning Deep Architectures for AI that was published in 2009</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper by proposing a new training principle for denoising autoencoders that enhances the robustness of learned representations, thereby extending the discussion on deep architectures and feature learning. It also includes comparative experiments that demonstrate the advantages of its approach over existing methods, which are likely influenced by the foundational ideas presented in the parent paper.</data>
