      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deep Sparse Rectifier Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Learning Deep Architectures for AI,&quot; by exploring the performance of rectifying neural networks in the context of deep architectures. It extends the parent paper's discussion on deep learning by specifically addressing the advantages of sparse representations and non-linearities in neural network training.</data>
