      <data key="d3">In 2010, article Stacked Denoising Autoencoders: Learning Useful Representations in a Deep Network with a Local Denoising Criterion was published and referenced article Learning Deep Architectures for AI that was published in 2009</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Stacked Denoising Autoencoders,&quot; builds on the concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Learning Deep Architectures for AI,&quot; by proposing a specific method for constructing deep networks using stacked denoising autoencoders. It extends the parent paper's discussion on deep architectures by demonstrating how this approach can achieve lower error rates in classification tasks and improve feature learning in a purely unsupervised manner.</data>
