      <data key="d3">In 2016, article Asynchronous Methods for Deep Reinforcement Learning was published and referenced article Playing Atari with Deep Reinforcement Learning that was published in 2013</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by proposing an asynchronous framework for deep reinforcement learning that enhances the training stability and performance of existing algorithms, including those used in the parent paper's Atari domain experiments. It extends the findings of the parent paper by demonstrating improved results in both Atari games and continuous motor control tasks.</data>
