    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2508457857" target="https://openalex.org/W2153663612">
      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Beyond a Gaussian Denoiser: Residual Learning of Deep CNN for Image Denoising was published and referenced article Image Denoising Via Sparse and Redundant Representations Over Learned Dictionaries that was published in 2006</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by advancing the field of image denoising through the introduction of a deep convolutional neural network (DnCNN) that addresses limitations of traditional methods, such as those presented in the parent paper, by enabling blind denoising and improving training efficiency. While the parent paper focuses on sparse representations and learned dictionaries, the child paper extends these concepts by incorporating deep learning techniques to enhance performance across multiple image restoration tasks.</data>
      <data key="d5">6</data>
      <data key="d6">G1722</data>
