    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2121058967" target="https://openalex.org/W2153663612">
      <data key="d3">In 2010, article Image Super-Resolution Via Sparse Representation was published and referenced article Image Denoising Via Sparse and Redundant Representations Over Learned Dictionaries that was published in 2006</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by applying the concept of sparse representation and learned dictionaries to the problem of single-image super-resolution, extending the theoretical framework and methodologies introduced in the parent paper to achieve improved image quality and computational efficiency. While both papers focus on sparse representations, the child paper specifically adapts and innovates upon the techniques of the parent paper to address the distinct challenge of super-resolution rather than denoising.</data>
      <data key="d5">7</data>
      <data key="d6">G1724</data>
