    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2965373594" target="https://openalex.org/W2970597249">
      <data key="d3">In 2019, article RoBERTa: A Robustly Optimized BERT Pretraining Approach was published and referenced article XLNet: Generalized Autoregressive Pretraining for Language Understanding that was published in 2019</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;RoBERTa: A Robustly Optimized BERT Pretraining Approach,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;XLNet: Generalized Autoregressive Pretraining for Language Understanding,&quot; by conducting a replication study of BERT and emphasizing the importance of hyperparameter tuning and training data size, ultimately demonstrating improved performance metrics. While it references the parent paper, it primarily extends the discussion on language model pretraining rather than directly comparing performance with XLNet.</data>
      <data key="d5">6</data>
      <data key="d6">G1725</data>
