    <edge source="https://openalex.org/W2979826702" target="https://openalex.org/W2970597249">
      <data key="d3">In 2020, article Transformers: State-of-the-Art Natural Language Processing was published and referenced article XLNet: Generalized Autoregressive Pretraining for Language Understanding that was published in 2019</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Transformers: State-of-the-Art Natural Language Processing,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;XLNet: Generalized Autoregressive Pretraining for Language Understanding,&quot; by leveraging the advancements in transformer architectures and their applications in natural language processing tasks. It extends the discussion of language models by showcasing the state-of-the-art performance achieved through transformer-based approaches, including those influenced by XLNet's methodologies.</data>
