      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by applying recurrent neural network (RNN) techniques, specifically Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, to sequence-to-sequence learning tasks, such as machine translation. It extends the findings of the parent paper by demonstrating improved performance on translation tasks while addressing challenges related to long sentences and out-of-vocabulary words.</data>
