      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Photo-Realistic Single Image Super-Resolution Using a Generative Adversarial Network was published and referenced article Real-Time Single Image and Video Super-Resolution Using an Efficient Sub-Pixel Convolutional Neural Network that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Photo-Realistic Single Image Super-Resolution Using a Generative Adversarial Network,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of single image super-resolution presented in the parent paper, &quot;Real-Time Single Image and Video Super-Resolution Using an Efficient Sub-Pixel Convolutional Neural Network,&quot; by introducing a novel generative adversarial network (GAN) approach that aims to enhance texture detail and perceptual quality beyond the capabilities of the parent paper's methods. While the parent paper focuses on real-time performance and efficiency, the child paper extends this work by addressing the challenge of recovering finer textures at larger upscaling factors through a new perceptual loss function.</data>
