      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Enhanced Deep Residual Networks for Single Image Super-Resolution,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts presented in the parent paper, &quot;Real-Time Single Image and Video Super-Resolution Using an Efficient Sub-Pixel Convolutional Neural Network,&quot; by introducing an enhanced network architecture that optimizes performance through the removal of unnecessary modules and the implementation of a multi-scale system. While both papers address single image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, the child paper extends the parent paper's work by proposing improvements that achieve superior results in benchmark datasets.</data>
