      <data key="d3">In 2018, article The Unreasonable Effectiveness of Deep Features as a Perceptual Metric was published and referenced article Enhanced Deep Residual Networks for Single Image Super-Resolution that was published in 2017</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by evaluating the effectiveness of deep features as a perceptual metric in image synthesis, comparing its findings with traditional metrics and demonstrating that deep features outperform them significantly. While the parent paper focuses on enhancing deep residual networks for single image super-resolution, the child paper extends this work by exploring the implications of deep learning features in assessing perceptual similarity, thus contributing to the understanding of visual representations in computer vision.</data>
