      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;EfficientDet: Scalable and Efficient Object Detection,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Path Aggregation Network for Instance Segmentation,&quot; by proposing optimizations for object detection that enhance model efficiency and performance. While the parent paper focuses on improving instance segmentation through feature propagation, the child paper extends this work by introducing a new family of detectors that leverage these architectural insights to achieve state-of-the-art results in object detection.</data>
