      <data key="d3">In 2014, article Empirical Evaluation of Gated Recurrent Neural Networks on Sequence Modeling was published and referenced article On the Properties of Neural Machine Translation: Encoder–Decoder Approaches that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper empirically evaluates and compares the performance of gated recurrent neural networks (GRUs and LSTMs) against traditional RNN units, building on the foundational concepts of recurrent neural networks discussed in the parent paper. While it does not directly extend the parent paper's findings on neural machine translation, it utilizes similar neural network architectures to explore their effectiveness in sequence modeling tasks.</data>
