      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Towards Evaluating the Robustness of Neural Networks was published and referenced article Explaining and Harnessing Adversarial Examples that was published in 2014</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Towards Evaluating the Robustness of Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Explaining and Harnessing Adversarial Examples,&quot; by evaluating the effectiveness of defensive distillation against adversarial attacks, thereby extending the discussion on neural network vulnerabilities and robustness. It specifically critiques the robustness claims made in the parent paper by demonstrating that defensive strategies can still be compromised, thus contributing to the ongoing discourse on adversarial machine learning.</data>
