      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;DeepFool: A Simple and Accurate Method to Fool Deep Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Explaining and Harnessing Adversarial Examples,&quot; by proposing the DeepFool algorithm as an effective method to generate adversarial examples and quantify the robustness of deep neural networks. It extends the parent paper's discussion on adversarial vulnerabilities by providing a new approach that outperforms existing methods in computing adversarial perturbations.</data>
