      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Unpaired Image-to-Image Translation Using Cycle-Consistent Adversarial Networks was published and referenced article Image Style Transfer Using Convolutional Neural Networks that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Unpaired Image-to-Image Translation Using Cycle-Consistent Adversarial Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Image Style Transfer Using Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; by extending the idea of image style transfer to scenarios where paired training data is unavailable, utilizing cycle consistency to enhance the translation process. While both papers address image manipulation and style transfer, the child paper introduces a novel approach that addresses the limitations of the parent paper's reliance on paired data.</data>
