      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Photo-Realistic Single Image Super-Resolution Using a Generative Adversarial Network,&quot; builds on the foundational concepts of image representation and manipulation introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Image Style Transfer Using Convolutional Neural Networks,&quot; by applying advanced techniques in generative adversarial networks to enhance the quality of super-resolved images. While both papers explore image processing through deep learning, the child paper specifically extends the parent paper's ideas to address the challenge of recovering finer texture details in single image super-resolution.</data>
