      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by introducing a novel adaptive instance normalization (AdaIN) layer that enables real-time arbitrary style transfer, addressing the limitations of the parent paper's slower iterative optimization process. While both papers focus on style transfer using neural networks, the child paper extends the parent’s framework by allowing for flexible user controls and faster performance without being restricted to predefined styles.</data>
