      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by proposing a deep learning method for single image super-resolution that extends the concepts of sparse representation by optimizing all layers of a convolutional neural network (CNN) instead of handling components separately. While the parent paper focuses on sparse signal representation, the child paper enhances the approach by achieving state-of-the-art restoration quality and faster processing speeds through a unified deep learning framework.</data>
