      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by extending the concepts of image processing and representation to the domain of image denoising using deep convolutional neural networks (DnCNNs). While the parent paper focuses on super-resolution through sparse representation, the child paper introduces a novel approach that incorporates residual learning and blind denoising, demonstrating advancements in performance and methodology.</data>
