      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by introducing a novel convolutional neural network architecture for real-time single image and video super-resolution, which improves upon the sparse representation approach of the parent paper by replacing handcrafted filters with learned upscaling filters. Additionally, the child paper demonstrates significant performance improvements in both reconstruction accuracy and computational efficiency compared to the methods discussed in the parent paper.</data>
