      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Non-local Neural Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Long-term recurrent convolutional networks for visual recognition and description,&quot; by proposing a new non-local operation that captures long-range dependencies, which enhances the performance of various vision architectures, including those discussed in the parent paper. While the parent paper focuses on recurrent architectures for temporal tasks, the child paper extends this work by introducing a method that can be integrated into existing models to improve their effectiveness in video classification and other visual recognition tasks.</data>
