      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by analyzing the limitations of standard gradient descent in training deep feedforward neural networks and proposing a new scheme for faster convergence, while referencing the parent paper's greedy layer-wise training approach as a foundational concept. It extends the discussion by investigating the effects of activation functions and gradient behavior across layers, thereby contributing to the understanding of deep network training dynamics.</data>
