      <data key="d3">In 2017, article Xception: Deep Learning with Depthwise Separable Convolutions was published and referenced article Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Xception: Deep Learning with Depthwise Separable Convolutions,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning,&quot; by proposing a novel architecture that replaces traditional convolutions with depthwise separable convolutions, thereby extending the Inception framework. While it demonstrates improved performance on the ImageNet dataset, it does so by leveraging insights from the parent paper rather than merely comparing results.</data>
