      <data key="d3">In 2016, article SqueezeNet: AlexNet-level accuracy with 50x fewer parameters and &lt;0.5MB model size was published and referenced article Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning that was published in 2016</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;SqueezeNet,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning,&quot; by proposing a new architecture that achieves comparable accuracy to AlexNet while significantly reducing the number of parameters and model size. It extends the discussion on efficient deep neural network architectures by emphasizing the advantages of smaller models in practical applications, thereby inheriting and advancing the foundational ideas of performance optimization in deep learning.</data>
