      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the parent paper by introducing a novel architectural search space (&quot;NASNet space&quot;) and a regularization technique (&quot;ScheduledDropPath&quot;) that enhance the performance of neural network models for image recognition, while also achieving state-of-the-art results. It extends the concepts of architecture design and performance evaluation established in the parent paper, particularly in the context of scalable image recognition.</data>
