      <data key="d4">The child paper, &quot;Deformable Convolutional Networks,&quot; builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper, &quot;Inception-v4, Inception-ResNet and the Impact of Residual Connections on Learning,&quot; by enhancing the transformation modeling capabilities of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) through the introduction of deformable convolution and RoI pooling modules. While the parent paper focuses on the benefits of residual connections in deep networks, the child paper extends this foundation by proposing new methods that improve CNN performance on complex vision tasks.</data>
