      <data key="d3">In 1992, article A training algorithm for optimal margin classifiers was published and referenced article Neural Networks and the Bias/Variance Dilemma that was published in 1992</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper by proposing a new training algorithm for optimal margin classifiers, which addresses the challenges of classification and generalization performance in machine learning. While the parent paper discusses the limitations of feedforward neural networks, the child paper extends this discussion by presenting an alternative approach that maximizes the margin between patterns and decision boundaries, demonstrating its effectiveness through experimental results.</data>
