      <data key="d3">In 2006, article Semi-Supervised Learning was published and referenced article Neural Networks and the Bias/Variance Dilemma that was published in 1992</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper on Semi-Supervised Learning builds on the foundational concepts of machine learning discussed in the parent paper on Neural Networks and the Bias/Variance Dilemma, particularly in its exploration of classification problems and algorithmic strategies. While the parent paper focuses on neural network models and their limitations, the child paper extends this discussion by reviewing state-of-the-art algorithms and applications in the context of semi-supervised learning, thereby inheriting and expanding upon the theoretical framework established in the parent work.</data>
