      <data key="d3">In 2001, article An introduction to kernel-based learning algorithms was published and referenced article Neural Networks and the Bias/Variance Dilemma that was published in 1992</data>
      <data key="d4">The child paper builds on the concepts introduced in the parent paper by discussing kernel-based learning algorithms, which can be seen as an alternative approach to the neural networks and bias/variance dilemma addressed in the parent paper. While the parent paper focuses on the limitations of feedforward neural networks, the child paper expands the discussion to include kernel methods, thereby extending the theoretical framework of machine learning.</data>
